commit_message:
Fix delorean_hash for newton and ocata promotion

Currently delorean_hash used for newton and ocata promotion
is set to "consistent" in promotion-testing-hash-$RELEASE.yml
which is wrong. Set it to "tripleo-ci-testing".

Change-Id: Iecb934f652f76d83289addb329ec8096559e215f

commit_message:
Remove ceph::rgw::apache

ceph::rgw::apache was deprecated in Hammer and the upstream puppetlabs
apache module has removed support for fastcgi in EL7. This change
removes the redhat tests around this as well as removing the
ceph::rgw::apache class.

Co-Authored-By: Alex Schultz <aschultz@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I009e3717e9e5c7887a2898dffa65079d61caadca

commit_message:
Add openstack/requirements to publish-openstack-python-branch-tarball

Many projects embed a zuul-cloner directive in their
tools/tox_install.sh script in order to retrieve
openstack/requirements [1]. This causes the playbook
'python-tarball/run.yaml' to fail installing the project and
failing the tarball publishing jobs such as here [2]

Sync list of required projects with release-openstack-python job.

[1]: http://codesearch.openstack.org/?q=openstack%2Frequirements&i=nope&files=tools%2Ftox_install.sh&repos=
[2]: http://logs.openstack.org/e9/e95351593168da9ae6c55c8b5995c097d0ba7853/post/publish-openstack-python-branch-tarball/03c4f4b/ara/

Co-Authored-By: David Moreau-Simard <dmsimard@redhat.com>
Change-Id: Iaf38b21e5a8a4283285780f3fb384b07348755e9

commit_message:
Set display-name for WSGI

In order to see all the processes named correctly based
on their origins we should set display-name so all the WSGI
processes are named difrerently from the Apache ones.

Change-Id: I123530014c973e7312a18e384a2c0159842bf228
Closes-bug: #1726841

commit_message:
Allow running mistral-api service via wsgi in container

A review to add the necessary packages to run mistral-api via wsgi was
proposed to kolla in I07ffd0b398e20065fff27c30d0842b94090ca0ad but this
is unlikely we'll be able to backport to stable/pike due to the nature
of the change.

So make the necessary change in our override file so we have more
freedom to backport.

Change-Id: Id2bfb6ba761821616301f996dd68fea8f07ae5f3
Related-Bug: #1724607

commit_message:
Don't append DockerInsecureRegistryAddress

This is no longer required as the prepare command detects whether the
registry is secure and DockerInsecureRegistryAddress as necessary.

Change-Id: Ieac6b4b2a7ab81688d1dc4315c312eef8be500c9
Depends-On: I74586145c222921880402cec92bbaa5f10e8b972
Related-Bug: #1722632

commit_message:
Force the installation of qemu packages

When doing upgrades after adding a new apt channel (like UCA),
the apt module will upgrade the directly listed packages, and its
recommended packages, not the child dependencies.

You could arrive to a state where qemu-system-x86 was installed
but not upgraded, while qemu-system and qemu-block-extra:amd64
would be upgraded. This could lead to compute issues.

Change-Id: Ifa474634ebde4cabfded273739eaac5278b63901
Closes-Bug: #1716908

commit_message:
Add os_congress role to openstack-ansible

This patch adds a preseeded repository to OpenStack-Ansible for
deploying Congress.

This project will have its own core team with the general
openstack-ansible core team included, with the appropriate rights to
ensure that they can act as a back-stop in case of any issues.

Needed-By: I8847b91e6e791a1e787b4e25b0422cadda43c41c
Change-Id: If63290eb7e8f4f14b627ff383a5747499f307446

'}, {'created': '2017-11-01 10:09:45.000000000', 'message': 'Add cross-repo base job and fix log collection

In order to facilitate cross-repo testing, this adds a base
job which can be used to define other jobs which make use of
the tests from another OSA repo.

When zuul executes jobs it adds all the post plays together
and executes them in the inherited sequence. This is causing
some confusion in our cross-repo testing where the logs are
trying to be collected twice as the cross-repo test is based
on the standard functional test.

Instead of defining two sets of plays we can consolidate them
into a single set, eliminating the confusion and repetition.

At the same time we also do not try to collect logs if the
script to prepare them was not able to execute, and we fix
the conditional for the ARA report generation so that it
works properly with the value being given it by zuul which
is a boolean word. To make sure it still works outside of
Zuul we leave the conditional which uses the standard success
return code of 0.

Consolidated backport of:
- https://review.openstack.org/513453
- https://review.openstack.org/516723

Change-Id: If39e4bec8db0be04b13dfc005ee404b73c0b65d3
'}]
commit_message:
Add cross-repo base job and fix log collection

In order to facilitate cross-repo testing, this adds a base
job which can be used to define other jobs which make use of
the tests from another OSA repo.

When zuul executes jobs it adds all the post plays together
and executes them in the inherited sequence. This is causing
some confusion in our cross-repo testing where the logs are
trying to be collected twice as the cross-repo test is based
on the standard functional test.

Instead of defining two sets of plays we can consolidate them
into a single set, eliminating the confusion and repetition.

At the same time we also do not try to collect logs if the
script to prepare them was not able to execute, and we fix
the conditional for the ARA report generation so that it
works properly with the value being given it by zuul which
is a boolean word. To make sure it still works outside of
Zuul we leave the conditional which uses the standard success
return code of 0.

Consolidated backport of:
- https://review.openstack.org/513453
- https://review.openstack.org/516723

Change-Id: If39e4bec8db0be04b13dfc005ee404b73c0b65d3

commit_message:
Correct validation of RAID config in functional tests

Both raid_config and target_raid_config are objects, not strings.
I suspect it only works now because the default API version is too old
for RAID config. It breaks when the version is bumped.

Change-Id: I4e911922ec9d0b446c5e45d2af6ac4565f228889

commit_message:
Pass requested_destination in filter_properties

When we added the requested_destination field for the RequestSpec object
in Newton, we forgot to pass it to the legacy dictionary when wanting to
use scheduler methods not yet supporting the NovaObject.
As a consequence, when we were transforming the RequestSpec object into a
tuple of (request_spec, filter_props) dicts and then rehydrating a new
RequestSpec object using those dicts, the newly created object was not
keeping that requested_destination field from the original.

Change-Id: Iba0b88172e9a3bfd4f216dd364d70f7e01c60ee2
Closes-Bug: #1702454

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

commit_message:
Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

Change-Id: I475a5ac24f025fb120fcc57579be62d98b5c3d2c

commit_message:
Append group permissions instead of clearing them

We set the groups for the syslog user to be "adm", but this will clear
any existing groups. That will mess with permissions in cases where we
want syslog to be in other groups for the ability to handle a different
applications logging.

Change-Id: If267cfd2f3f8f182c396e3f2836ec7e1d572fe0a
(cherry picked from commit 3b917569cda50cbd491b3b86b4313100171962bf)

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: Iebac2702a8325e407099e9caa5a13a59eaefe800

commit_message:
Remove the runtime constraint

This patch fixes the problem where the runtime
had only choice "runc" and no other custom runtimes
were not allowed. Now Zun supports running any
custom runtime.

Change-Id: I38efb4bee4aa7176ebfdcd3b5e817156a5f0f22d

commit_message:
Use icmpv6 instead of ipv6-icmp

A change in puppetlabs-firewall [1] changed the interface to only accept
icmpv6 instead of ipv6-icmp, and this broke us.

[1] https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-firewall/commit/41fb8205b68aec8a3683e1b4f53ec9de2246d504

Closes-Bug: #1720918
Change-Id: I212d8073bb4f36a4de171e0ada5145b1cdd6c4d6

commit_message:
Fix openstack-infra publishing

Add native zuul v3 job to publish index file of
openstack-infra/publications.
Run the post job on all branches, so that a change to the master branch
regenerates the index file.

Add native zuul v3 job to publish a specific publication from
openstack-infra/publications.
Use the job for the project.

Needed-By: I190b34217c87d45e13bca18c7e121189323b698f
Change-Id: I6da66649726a1a96d06d7ca643adeec8ea8649eb

commit_message:
use FAULT_MAP from neutron-lib

The FAULT_MAP is now located in neutron-lib and will be removed from
neutron with Ib051555ea8496ed7eec8ed30733c964012e31c32
This patch updates imports to use neutron-lib's FAULT_MAP.

Change-Id: Ie5639a39dac4a52bbe294b637c0dd5f92f6ef475
Depends-On: I8e79f29206ec244d870e19f99c18ccaaa50b4761

commit_message:
Chart Runner: Add NFS provisoner and Docker Registry

This PS adds the NFS provisioner and Docker Registry to the OSH-Infra Repo,
these are being used as initial candidates for moving as they are simple
charts and allow the chart runner logic to be developed in the gate
playbooks.

Change-Id: Ie80b8578aafd3fe7252d3dcb603ea6af7586776e

commit_message:
Kubernetes: widen nodeport range and serve statistics

This PS widens the range for nodeports, allowing standard OpenStack
ports to be used if desired for ingress.

Additionally the controller manager is set to serve statistics on the
standard port.

Change-Id: Id6549e90491a79c1ac6830a1324db7f13c88ea13

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-01 17:21:37.000000000', 'message': 'Revert "tripleo: index /var/log/*.log.txt files"

This reverts commit 1f4d096c346368d15869265e5a08ad93289e20dc.

to be some bugs with this like indexing all of these log files as

try to move forward with this more carefully ensuring that crm114 is
ready and that we know what we are indexing and apply the correct tags
to it.

commit_message:
Revert "tripleo: index /var/log/*.log.txt files"

This reverts commit 1f4d096c346368d15869265e5a08ad93289e20dc.

We are reverting this as it appears to significantly add to the total
number of files being indexed and we are very behind. Also there appear
to be some bugs with this like indexing all of these log files as
console logs when many of them are openstack service logs.

Additionally this seems to have caused crm114 to fill up its disks as it
creates a new dir with learning data on disk for each unique file path.
We will need to update crm114 to better collapse files into things that
are less unique.

Reverting this allows us to take a step back and stabilize then we can
try to move forward with this more carefully ensuring that crm114 is
ready and that we know what we are indexing and apply the correct tags
to it.

Change-Id: Ie75d13f4275d74c7035e6b8f89bab47d1b053d03

The glance, nova, neutron, and cinder playbooks are run in serial and
represent the bulk of deployment time on both greenfield and upgrades.
Because these playbooks use a lot of serialization the execution time on
large deployments is exaggerated. This commit changes the playbooks so
that they'll look for their respective directory within /etc/ and if
it's not found the host will be placed into a bulk group which will
install all services in parallel. If the directory is found the playbook
will continue using our desired serialization to ensure we're carefully
handling our upgrade use cases.

commit_message:
Improve execution time by using dynamic groups

The glance, nova, neutron, and cinder playbooks are run in serial and
represent the bulk of deployment time on both greenfield and upgrades.
Because these playbooks use a lot of serialization the execution time on
large deployments is exaggerated. This commit changes the playbooks so
that they'll look for their respective directory within /etc/ and if
it's not found the host will be placed into a bulk group which will
install all services in parallel. If the directory is found the playbook
will continue using our desired serialization to ensure we're carefully
handling our upgrade use cases.

The new bulk processing group has been added after our serialized groups
so that we're correctly supporting the bulk addition of new nodes into a
cloud without negatively impacting running services. This is especially
true when adding nodes and upgrading services, intra-series or major, at
the same time.

If a deployer wishes all services simply run in bulk instead of serial
they can now set a new option, `os_force_bulk`, to "true" to force all
service hosts into the bulk group.

Change-Id: I770e476daf2511bd5033571a5816bbf156dd87bc
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Backport zuul jobs, use newton-eol

With latest changes to Zuul, we need to backport the jobs as well
from master.

Do not include translation jobs, those are not run on newton anymore.
This also removes unused jobs and templates.

Also, fix stable/newton to newton-eol so that this builds.

Change-Id: I4189d5d3378dba68eb2d0a4119fa48aa03c3ec45

commit_message:
Remove new retired projects from update bot

Update bot should not try to update repos that have been retired.
os_freezer being newly retired, we exclude it from the proposal
bot script using our exclude list.

Change-Id: I502d87e565df86b1c48d5c1c24890f9a349e122b

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Depends-On: I0391ec310c4eede436011a48490e3c524c8ddf4d
Change-Id: I62cefde6f4b473a74f46d8f7f2a10adfdcded779

commit_message:
Use generic stable periodic jobs

Instead of having separate templates for each branch, use a single
template - together with a neutron variant - for the stable periodic
jobs and add the required branch conditions here.

Once this is in, we can use it in project-config.

commit_message:
Add os_congress role to openstack-ansible

This patch adds a preseeded repository to OpenStack-Ansible for
deploying Congress.

This project will have its own core team with the general
openstack-ansible core team included, with the appropriate rights to
ensure that they can act as a back-stop in case of any issues.

Needed-By: I8847b91e6e791a1e787b4e25b0422cadda43c41c
Change-Id: I76460bb6a0f9aaf8a8d60509fb4f84b977d8e6ed

subject: Remove the continue option for aria2c
messages: [{'account_id': 6816, 'date': '2017-11-01 10:57:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Cherry Picked from branch master.'}, {'account_id': 17068, 'date': '2017-11-01 11:01:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 7353, 'date': '2017-11-01 16:39:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-01 10:57:44.000000000', 'message': "Remove the continue option for aria2c

The continue option doesn't handle correcly updating file.
When using the --continue option with aria2c if the file exist it will try to
update the current file, if the remote file change (eg.: start the task on
friday and restart it monday when you come back to the office), the remote file
will probably change since image a generated daily and can result in a corrupted
archive.

From the manpage, the continue option is used to resume is to resume a download
which was started by another program. it's not quite the case here.

We could also have a handler to remove files when the task fail but it would
result in the same thing as the file will need to be re-downloaded entirely.

Change-Id: Ia3201e4dba1fa9b99eaff9986fbbdbc37e139b7f
(cherry picked from commit 2a6654398a279dbee3e88f7f58c1ceffbd04b27b)
"}]
commit_message:
Remove the continue option for aria2c

The continue option doesn't handle correcly updating file.
When using the --continue option with aria2c if the file exist it will try to
update the current file, if the remote file change (eg.: start the task on
friday and restart it monday when you come back to the office), the remote file
will probably change since image a generated daily and can result in a corrupted
archive.

From the manpage, the continue option is used to resume is to resume a download
which was started by another program. it's not quite the case here.

We could also have a handler to remove files when the task fail but it would
result in the same thing as the file will need to be re-downloaded entirely.

Change-Id: Ia3201e4dba1fa9b99eaff9986fbbdbc37e139b7f
(cherry picked from commit 2a6654398a279dbee3e88f7f58c1ceffbd04b27b)

commit_message:
tasks: lxc_cache_preparation: Log cache preparation command output

We already enable debug output (-x) in the shell script but we never
actually see this output during or after the cache preparation step
takes place. It's useful to log what exactly happened so we can look
for problems or find potential optimization opportunities so just log
the output to /var/log which is also being collected by the various CI
scripts.

Change-Id: I3d0ab31e052889b9ac03de9a3ccba680e840fca5
(cherry picked from commit f00824fa8c4514aacb4d0495332568bf243c1fbf)

commit_message:
Add OpenStack-Ansible metadata

We need to add openstack ansible information in the role
metadata to be able to track role maturity. With it,
we can create a role maturity table and take decisions about
role deprecations.

The role status is "unmaintained". During our last community
meeting, we've decided to move this role that has receive no
commits for 4 months, to this state.

Change-Id: I081174fe6fa840a756a723c862581103ca0909ca

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: I0ffe734e8da524df6a173ea12f3e990488eb0c82

commit_message:
Reword interface information in multitenancy docs

There has been some confusion about the difference between the flat and
neutron network interfaces. This patch aims to improve the descriptions
of those interfaces to explain the differences and behaviours better.

commit_message:
Retiring old OpenStack-Ansible projects

This is the phase 1 of the retirement of both pip_lock_down
and the openstack-ansible-os_freezer roles.

The former one is not in use since many cycles, while the
latter never had the developer uptake, so we decided
to mark it as unmaintained during our last community
meeting.

Change-Id: Id6109524a8435d90a47b85f31e434716ecd33ac1

[{'created': '2017-10-31 01:55:53.000000000', 'message': "Move async wait to a later position for role performance

The async wait we're doing can be moved elsewhere in the role so that
we're able to do more in parallel. This change simply moves the async
wait to a postition just before its required.

Change-Id: I26eae11be8f7d5b691fbccd3d2fe1cfb21b8cf55
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
"}, {'created': '2017-10-31 04:20:56.000000000', 'message': "Update role for efficiency and to make better use modules

The LXC host role can be tuned up for better overall efficiency.

Highlights:
* Move async wait to a later position for role performance. The
  async wait we're doing can be moved elsewhere in the role so
  that we're able to do more in parallel. This change simply moves
  the async wait to a postition just before its required.
* Move container creation tasks into their own sub-files which are
  accessed using dynamic routing.
* Several syntatic items were cleaned up.
* All of the basic cache cleanup has been moved to handlers.

Change-Id: I26eae11be8f7d5b691fbccd3d2fe1cfb21b8cf55

commit_message:
Update role for efficiency and to make better use modules

The LXC host role can be tuned up for better overall efficiency.

Highlights:
* Move async wait to a later position for role performance. The
  async wait we're doing can be moved elsewhere in the role so
  that we're able to do more in parallel. This change simply moves
  the async wait to a postition just before its required.
* Move container creation tasks into their own sub-files which are
  accessed using dynamic routing.
* Several syntatic items were cleaned up.
* All of the basic cache cleanup has been moved to handlers.

Closes-Bug: #1718979
Change-Id: I26eae11be8f7d5b691fbccd3d2fe1cfb21b8cf55
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Consolidate IP address configuration

There are several IP address / hostname related configs (i.e. api.host_ip,
docker.docker_remote_api_host, websocket_proxy.wsproxy_host) that required
manual configuration by operators. Normally, these configs are default as
local IP / hostname. It is undesirable for operators to tune all these configs
repeatedly. Let's consolidate all these configurations into two defaults:

* [DEFAULT] my_ip: The IP address which the host is using to connect to the
* management network.
* [DEFAULT] host: Hostname, FQDN or IP address of this host.

Change-Id: Ie26578c4208a79e4306b1006c6b316a41c2b3540
Closes-Bug: #1723515

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-12 15:41:05.000000000', 'message': 'Add --detailed-exitcodes when running puppet on the host via ansible

puppet run on the host never fails, even when it should, since we moved
to the ansible way of applying it. The reason is the current following code:

    - name: Run puppet host configuration for step {{step}}
      command: >-
        puppet apply
        --modulepath=/etc/puppet/modules:/opt/stack/puppet-modules:/usr/share/openstack-puppet/modules
        --logdest syslog --logdest console --color=false
        /var/lib/tripleo-config/puppet_step_config.pp

The above is missing the --detailed-exitcodes switch and so puppet will never
really error out on us and the deployment will keep on running all the
steps even though a previous puppet manifest might have failed. This
cause extra hard-to-debug failures.

Co-Authored-By: Damien Ciabrini <dciabrin@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Ie9df4f520645404560a9635fb66e3af42b966f54
Closes-Bug: #1723163
'}, {'created': '2017-10-12 15:47:15.000000000', 'message': "Add --detailed-exitcodes when running puppet via ansible

puppet run on never fails, even when it should, since we moved
to the ansible way of applying it. The reason is the current following code:

    - name: Run puppet host configuration for step {{step}}
      command: >-
        puppet apply
        --modulepath=/etc/puppet/modules:/opt/stack/puppet-modules:/usr/share/openstack-puppet/modules
        --logdest syslog --logdest console --color=false
        /var/lib/tripleo-config/puppet_step_config.pp

The above is missing the --detailed-exitcodes switch and so puppet will never
really error out on us and the deployment will keep on running all the
steps even though a previous puppet manifest might have failed. This
cause extra hard-to-debug failures.

Initially the issue was observed on the puppet host runs, but this
parameter is missing also from docker-puppet.py, so let's add it there
as well as it makes sense to return proper error codes whenever we call
puppet.

Co-Authored-By: Damien Ciabrini <dciabrin@redhat.com>

"}, {'created': '2017-10-12 15:59:34.000000000', 'message': "Add --detailed-exitcodes when running puppet via ansible

puppet run on never fails, even when it should, since we moved
to the ansible way of applying it. The reason is the current following code:

    - name: Run puppet host configuration for step {{step}}
      command: >-
        puppet apply
        --modulepath=/etc/puppet/modules:/opt/stack/puppet-modules:/usr/share/openstack-puppet/modules
        --logdest syslog --logdest console --color=false
        /var/lib/tripleo-config/puppet_step_config.pp

The above is missing the --detailed-exitcodes switch and so puppet will never
really error out on us and the deployment will keep on running all the
steps even though a previous puppet manifest might have failed. This
cause extra hard-to-debug failures.

Initially the issue was observed on the puppet host runs, but this
parameter is missing also from docker-puppet.py, so let's add it there
as well as it makes sense to return proper error codes whenever we call
puppet.

Co-Authored-By: Damien Ciabrini <dciabrin@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add --detailed-exitcodes when running puppet via ansible

puppet run on never fails, even when it should, since we moved
to the ansible way of applying it. The reason is the current following code:

    - name: Run puppet host configuration for step {{step}}
      command: >-
        puppet apply
        --modulepath=/etc/puppet/modules:/opt/stack/puppet-modules:/usr/share/openstack-puppet/modules
        --logdest syslog --logdest console --color=false
        /var/lib/tripleo-config/puppet_step_config.pp

The above is missing the --detailed-exitcodes switch and so puppet will never
really error out on us and the deployment will keep on running all the
steps even though a previous puppet manifest might have failed. This
cause extra hard-to-debug failures.

Initially the issue was observed on the puppet host runs, but this
parameter is missing also from docker-puppet.py, so let's add it there
as well as it makes sense to return proper error codes whenever we call
puppet.

Besides this being a good idea in general, we actually *have* to do it
because puppet does not fail correctly without this option due to the
following puppet bug:
https://tickets.puppetlabs.com/browse/PUP-2754

Depends-On: I607927c2ee5c29b605e18e9294b0f91d37337680
Co-Authored-By: Damien Ciabrini <dciabrin@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Ie9df4f520645404560a9635fb66e3af42b966f54
Closes-Bug: #1723163

commit_message:
Update timeout on openstack-tox-compare-cover job

Pre-Zuulv3 the compare cover job had a timeout of 75 minutes, to allow
for running the full UTs twice. This patch updates the zuulv3 job to
match that timeout.

Change-Id: I4955756e8cab4da931c572ecb23e389bd1a20011

commit_message:
Log a warning when trying to wait for metadata on a non existent port

As noticed in bug #1728088, we're receiving an 'up' event from a port
that does not exist. Even though we may want to prevent this from
happening, the current result is that we're throwing a confusing
exception because the chassis and datapath for this logical port can't
be retrieved.

This patch detects the above condition and logs a warning instead.

Related-Bug: #1728088

Change-Id: If15f457db6a99ba232e23349048fcbe2b1a4f36d
Signed-off-by: Daniel Alvarez <dalvarez@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Move legacy jobs into tree

This patch moves the legacy ironic-python-agent CI jobs into the
tree instead of storing them in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs
to give us control as we migrate the legacy jobs to the new ansible
roles.

Change-Id: I7f98258589954639fa8187a3fec4a0b9da05915d

commit_message:
SUSE: Use zypper's --force-resolution option when preparing the cache

Since we perform a full distribution update, some packages may be
removed, moved or conflict with new ones. As such, force zypper to come
up with a solution instead of waiting for user input.

Change-Id: Ibb3a5ba1d4d43bd70d908322b177abb7ed86876e
(cherry picked from commit d8f9887624d5634cfe3a11b4d8b883ae3d8e9acb)

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-01 11:22:40.000000000', 'message': "SUSE: Add ability to configure external mirror for openSUSE

Allow deployers to choose a specific mirror by setting the
'lxc_hosts_opensuse_mirror_url' variable

We need to delete all repos which do not match the expected ones so
we need an 'AND' conditional instead of 'OR'. Moreoever, all containers
are expected to have the cloud repository present. This is normally
being installed in the pip_install role but if the host has it already
then preserve that as well.

It's somewhat risky to assume that the host already has the default
repository files named as 'repo-oss' and 'repo-update'. In practise, these
repos could be named anything. If we install the same repo twice because
the filename differs, then strange things might happen. Lets just use
the zypper output to find out if the repos we care about are really
there. We also clean the metadata at the end and we start fresh.

The repositories were missing the .repo extension from the filename so
none of them was copied to the container chroot. Moreover, we should pass
the zypper repository directory as argument to the 'find' command and not
the repository files themselves.

Combined backport of:
- https://review.openstack.org/501650
- https://review.openstack.org/503084
- https://review.openstack.org/507106
- https://review.openstack.org/514850
- https://review.openstack.org/516625

Change-Id: If151501923c5308cfeaee6e33d12df3e7f6959d5
"}]
commit_message:
SUSE: Add ability to configure external mirror for openSUSE

Allow deployers to choose a specific mirror by setting the
'lxc_hosts_opensuse_mirror_url' variable

We need to delete all repos which do not match the expected ones so
we need an 'AND' conditional instead of 'OR'. Moreoever, all containers
are expected to have the cloud repository present. This is normally
being installed in the pip_install role but if the host has it already
then preserve that as well.

It's somewhat risky to assume that the host already has the default
repository files named as 'repo-oss' and 'repo-update'. In practise, these
repos could be named anything. If we install the same repo twice because
the filename differs, then strange things might happen. Lets just use
the zypper output to find out if the repos we care about are really
there. We also clean the metadata at the end and we start fresh.

The repositories were missing the .repo extension from the filename so
none of them was copied to the container chroot. Moreover, we should pass
the zypper repository directory as argument to the 'find' command and not
the repository files themselves.

Combined backport of:
- https://review.openstack.org/501650
- https://review.openstack.org/503084
- https://review.openstack.org/507106
- https://review.openstack.org/514850
- https://review.openstack.org/516625

Change-Id: If151501923c5308cfeaee6e33d12df3e7f6959d5

commit_message:
SUSE: Use the OBS Virtualization repository for lxc-2.X.X

openSUSE Leap ships lxc-1.1.5 which is rather old and unmaintained.
It's best to use the OBS development repository to get the latest
lxc-2.X.X which is the one maintained upstream.

Change-Id: I5a7baa3374bad67dcafc5c78f16b0dd4cae49ee4
(cherry picked from commit 12840676251e38e8125b7b204a350202d310d5fb)

commit_message:
XtremIO: fix fetching FC targets from X2 array

Previous versions of XtremIO had the type as part of the target name, in
X2 this convention was changed and a driver updated is required to query
the type from the target object.

Closes-Bug: #1702458
(cherry picked from commit 67facebe4d9996bcbe8b3aaffd0a0d78660649e7)

Change-Id: I1729a0b36c0ef5dbb4ed4f0655d7d1b91b86c692

So, thanks @Terry for taking a look into it!"}, {'account_id': 5756, 'date': '2017-10-24 17:38:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

I think, by definition, has_lock=True implies is_lock_contended=False and is_lock_contended=True implies has_lock=False (but both can obviously be False). Whenever one connection release the lock (which happens if the Idl goes away), ovsdb-server will notify one of the other Idl instances that it has the lock (setting has_lock=True/is_lock_contended=False). So I think checking both is redundant for the purpose of handling notifications and we can just check has_lock. Hopefully current me isn't missing something that past-me knew. :p

One other thing: set_lock() is called in from_server() and doesn't actually do anything until the first transaction is run (which calls idl.run() and goes until there is a change). We should probably add set/steal/unlock Commands to ovsdbapp and ensure that they are run in a transaction. If multiple things start at once, it looks like it might be possible for the first notification to show up in multiple places?"}, {'account_id': 21550, 'date': '2017-10-25 03:26:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Terry,thank you for your guidance;-)
has_lock=False may imply two conditions: a) not ask for a lock  or b) ask for a lock but not get it.
So i think check is_lock_contended may be better here?'}, {'account_id': 5756, 'date': '2017-10-25 13:03:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

In our case everything calls set_lock() on startup, but I agree that 'if is_lock_contended: return' is better than 'if not has_lock: return'."}, {'account_id': 21550, 'date': '2017-10-26 00:45:29.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2017-10-26 14:14:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

I think that if it closes a bug (and maybe we want to backport it) we could have a bug# and also a more explicit commit message for those like me who are not ovsdb experts. What do you guys think?"}, {'account_id': 11762, 'date': '2017-10-26 21:29:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Fix a redundant check about ovsdb lock in OvnWorker

'is_lock_contended': True, if the IDL is configured to obtain a lock
                     but the database server has indicated that
                     some other client already owns the requested lock,
                     and False otherwise.

is_lock_contended=True implies has_lock=False,
so checking both is redundant for the purpose of handling notifications.
I revise it by checking is_lock_contended rather than checking has_lock
because has_lock=False may not imply is_lock_contended=True when not
using set_lock.

Change-Id: I9aec09a558d79d3243c95d189d2afd55f626c71d

commit_message:
Fix log level on error applying DHCP options

This patch is changing the log level when an error occur applying the
DHCP options from INFO to ERROR. The INFO level is usually used when an
operation suceed in this case it should be an ERROR (not even a WARNING)
because without the DHCP options the node will not boot.

Closes-Bug: #1628634
Change-Id: Iba9b6d85c50dab8697cdc6349874ac8c9185ab4b

subject: Fix typo in spark-plugin.rst and recommendations_utils.py
messages:
[{'account_id': 26251, 'date': '2017-11-01 09:45:12.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 22689, 'date': '2017-11-01 12:21:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

Please avoid this kind of "typo" fix to save testing resource. And If you want to help Sahara become more stable, fixing bug in https://bugs.launchpad.net/sahara will be more helpful.'}, {'account_id': 8932, 'date': '2017-11-01 13:20:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Please if you are going to fix typos, try to gather a bunch in a single patch so we don't waste CI resources on simple patches like this. Don't work too hard on comments."}, {'account_id': 23078, 'date': '2017-11-01 14:16:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Hi sun cheng, in previous patches which you have submitted to Sahara, you can see that we warned you not to make such trivial patches. There are plenty of other meaningful ways to contribute.

As it stands, this patch only contains a "useful" change in the size of one character. I'll defer to other reviewers if that is still worth merging (after you undo the other mistaken change found in this patch).

You will find as you (hopefully) progress on your journey through the world of OpenStack, that people will never appreciate these kinds of patches. In general they are a waste of CI resources and a waste of reviewer time. Also, when you are fixing typos in code comments, remember that these strings are not read by end-users but only by developers. So, if there is a tiny typo in a comment it really does not matter as long as it is understood.

There is a great deal of honor which you can receive by contributing something meaningful to this or any other project. There is no honor in the kind of patch you are submitting now.'}, {'account_id': 26251, 'date': '2017-11-01 14:40:44.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Handling container on 'Deleting' state

If container is being deleting, we need to handle it correctly.
For example, avoid marking it as 'Error' and skip populating
information from docker.

Change-Id: I7fe7167d57bcd8ca8f902ec21b2eaca57911b14e

subject: Configure wsproxy base_url in devstack
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-17 21:27:37.000000000', 'message': "Configure wsproxy base_url in devstack

In devstack setup, zun-ui failed to attach to the container.
This is because the base_url is not configured and the default
value doesn't allow a remote attach. This patch fixed it.

Change-Id: Ie47e424c2e1542a290419df952019363711b9fd0
"}]
commit_message:
Configure wsproxy base_url in devstack

In devstack setup, zun-ui failed to attach to the container.
This is because the base_url is not configured and the default
value doesn't allow a remote attach. This patch fixed it.

Change-Id: Ie47e424c2e1542a290419df952019363711b9fd0

commit_message:
Make validation groups labels clickable

The validation list contains group labels for each group a validation
belongs to. Clicking these labels now adds a corresponding filter to the
ValidationsToolbar.

Change-Id: Ic4cc65cd345b9d5547b0434b5dbbf22bcc4cd170

commit_message:
AngularJS unittest with Jasmine and Karma

Change-Id: I3e42eac041d346851d51228f5e1185d8464325e9
Co-Authored-By: Saju Madhavan <sajuptpm@gmail.com>
Closes-Bug: 1670102

One of the action items in the queens-1 retrospective was to clearly
document our roadmap. Ideally, this is something specification should
do, but not all work in a release is associated to specifications.

This commit adds a link to the Queens roadmap next to the
accepted specifications for Queens. When Rocky opens for
development, we need to archive this link with the Queens
specifications so that it is discoverable.

'}]
commit_message:
Add link to Queens Roadmap

One of the action items in the queens-1 retrospective was to clearly
document our roadmap. Ideally, this is something specification should
do, but not all work in a release is associated to specifications.

This commit adds a link to the Queens roadmap next to the
accepted specifications for Queens. When Rocky opens for
development, we need to archive this link with the Queens
specifications so that it is discoverable.

Change-Id: I1a558abd0f7379a33a3176608aa55f9ba54390bb

commit_message:
Replace the usage of some aliases in tempest

In tempest, following aliases have been moved in version Pike
and will be removed in version Queens:
* manager > os_primary [1]
* admin_manager > os_admin [2]
* os_adm > os_admin [3]
* os > os_primary [4]
* alt_manager > os_alt [5]

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/468036/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/467852/
[3] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/467605/
[4] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/466991/
[5] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/457555/

Change-Id: If5b4322443d011c2264fdeff4eab83bee6a77c69

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-31 13:59:02.000000000', 'message': 'Ensure all pre-cloned git sources are found

Currently the find task only looks at one level deep
for repo folders, instead of the required three levels
deep.

Using the find module does not give us the ability to
set the depth level we want to do the find down to,
so we use a find command instead.

commit_message:
Ensure all pre-cloned git sources are found

Currently the find task only looks at one level deep
for repo folders, instead of the required three levels
deep.

Using the find module does not give us the ability to
set the depth level we want to do the find down to,
so we use a find command instead.

Change-Id: I0b218fe276292e13dbb40ab38c9a167025d16e45
(cherry picked from commit 56a4eb8adecfe005f6c31c6ebe00a91ecf297bae)

commit_message:
Relax last introspection lock

Currently the POST@/v1/introspection/<node_id> is protected by a last
introspection lock to prevent some BMCs from freaking out if is reboot
called too frequently.  This comprises an issue when the inspector is
being ran in multiple (HA) instances.

This patch relaxes the locking to a DB select: at least one node_info
object with the started_at attribute being too early ago.  The behaviour
changes from waiting in the background for the lock to expire to returning
the caller a 409 response.

Change-Id: Ibeddcbd7eb4285c6b3f560101bd6e9d034a6ed7d
Closes-Bug: 1729050

commit_message:
Allow to set default ifaces in DevStack

as we move toward deprecating classic drivers,
we need a way to specify which particular combination
of interfaces of a hw type to assign to nodes being enrolled
and run test against.

This patch adds a number of IRONIC_DEFAULT_<>_INTERFACE
variables to devstack plugin (all empty by default)
and if set, sets their value as "[DEFAULT]default_<>_interface"
config option.

Change-Id: I9fc22125ddd3c70ff37185d025df1dfa3217a782

[{'created': '2017-10-26 15:50:06.000000000', 'message': "Defer exceptions in calculating node_data()

When generating the node_data() for a resource, catch and store any
exceptions (other than InvalidTemplateAttribute) encountered while
getting attributes. Re-raise the exception at the point where we try to
read the attribute value, including where we try to serialise the
NodeData object to store in the database.

In convergence, we generate and immediately serialise the NodeData, so
this should result in no substantial change in behaviour there.

In other situations (e.g. when we're just loading the data to show the
stack), this prevents an error in attribute calculation from aborting
the whole operation. The exception will still be raised if (and only if)
the erroneous attribute is accessed, but may be handled more
appropriately. For example, errors in calculating output values are
handled by reporting an error only for that particular output.

Change-Id: Idc97aee87405cc13e83be3373078b52e725850ea

commit_message:
Defer exceptions in calculating node_data()

When generating the node_data() for a resource, catch and store any
exceptions (other than InvalidTemplateAttribute) encountered while
getting attributes. Re-raise the exception at the point where we try to
read the attribute value, including where we try to serialise the
NodeData object to store in the database.

In convergence, we generate and immediately serialise the NodeData, so
this should result in no substantial change in behaviour there.

In other situations (e.g. when we're just loading the data to show the
stack), this prevents an error in attribute calculation from aborting
the whole operation. The exception will still be raised if (and only if)
the erroneous attribute is accessed, but may be handled more
appropriately. For example, errors in calculating output values are
handled by reporting an error only for that particular output.

Change-Id: Idc97aee87405cc13e83be3373078b52e725850ea
Co-Authored-By: Zane Bitter <zbitter@redhat.com>
Closes-Bug: #1712280
(cherry picked from commit 4f4932c7900ae0e88e9a44f06b952c882474729e)

commit_message:
Don't attempt to escalate designate-manage privileges

Remove code which allowed designate-manage to attempt to escalate
privileges so that configuration files can be read by users who
normally wouldn't have access, but do have sudo access.

Simpler version of [1].

[1] I03063d2af14015e6506f1b6e958f5ff219aa4a87
Closes-Bug: 1611171

commit_message:
Don't run legacy-grenade-dsvm-neutron* jobs in newton or ocata

Neutron's newton branch is now EOL so we can't run neutron
grenade jobs in stable/newton or stable/ocata since newton won't
install.

Notes:

legacy-grenade-dsvm-neutron-forward is omitted since the grenade
forward job in ocata shouldn't be affected by newton-eol.

legacy-grenade-dsvm-neutron-multinode-live-migration and
legacy-grenade-dsvm-neutron-dvr-multinode branch
restrictions are pulled in from project-config and updated for
ocata.

legacy-grenade-dsvm-neutron-nova-next is removed since it was
pinned to stable/ocata in project-config and only makes sense
in a stable/ocata environment.

Depends-On: If56e8053a3b340d9770c52283900e091a7b02de5

Change-Id: I9f0421d4b3b821c710075a8532a255fd5851daa0

commit_message:
Add OpenStack-Ansible metadata

We need to add openstack ansible information in the role
metadata to be able to track role maturity. With it,
we can create a role maturity table and take decisions about
role deprecations.

The role maturity state is "incubated", conformly to our
role maturity guidelines. This role work has been started in
ocata and can therefore still have the incubated status in Pike.

Change-Id: Ia2ca7803115547931b452eee778afd02d3e54137

commit_message:
Add OpenStack-Ansible metadata

We need to add openstack ansible information in the role
metadata to be able to track role maturity. With it,
we can create a role maturity table and take decisions about
role deprecations.

The role maturity state is "incubated", conformly to our
role maturity guidelines. This role work has been started in
ocata and can therefore still have the incubated status in Pike.

Change-Id: Ia2ca7803115547931b452eee778afd02d3e54137

[{'created': '2017-09-01 13:31:44.000000000', 'message': "SUSE: Use the OBS Virtualization repository for lxc-2.X.X

openSUSE Leap ships lxc-1.1.5 which is rather old and unmaintained.
It's best to use the OBS development repository to get the latest
lxc-2.X.X which is the one maintained upstream.

Change-Id: I5a7baa3374bad67dcafc5c78f16b0dd4cae49ee4
"}]
commit_message:
SUSE: Use the OBS Virtualization repository for lxc-2.X.X

openSUSE Leap ships lxc-1.1.5 which is rather old and unmaintained.
It's best to use the OBS development repository to get the latest
lxc-2.X.X which is the one maintained upstream.

Change-Id: I5a7baa3374bad67dcafc5c78f16b0dd4cae49ee4

commit_message:
Calculate package directory correctly in pip_install

Strip the [<extras>] string from a <package_dir>[<extras>] argument
when looking for the package directory.  Explain what the heck is
going on.

Change-Id: I79beb5c3e9e7c35c91cdd0d5a1d91532bebc4b6d
Closes-Bug: #1721638
(cherry picked from commit 9e7ead9ac2e791f70542741aa2c84e7ad828ac7a)

commit_message:
Remove the continue option for aria2c

The continue option doesn't handle correcly updating file.
When using the --continue option with aria2c if the file exist it will try to
update the current file, if the remote file change (eg.: start the task on
friday and restart it monday when you come back to the office), the remote file
will probably change since image a generated daily and can result in a corrupted
archive.

From the manpage, the continue option is used to resume is to resume a download
which was started by another program. it's not quite the case here.

We could also have a handler to remove files when the task fail but it would
result in the same thing as the file will need to be re-downloaded entirely.

Change-Id: Ia3201e4dba1fa9b99eaff9986fbbdbc37e139b7f

commit_message:
SUSE: Use zypper's --force-resolution option when preparing the cache

Since we perform a full distribution update, some packages may be
removed, moved or conflict with new ones. As such, force zypper to come
up with a solution instead of waiting for user input.

Change-Id: Ibb3a5ba1d4d43bd70d908322b177abb7ed86876e

commit_message:
tasks: lxc_cache_preparation: Log cache preparation command output

We already enable debug output (-x) in the shell script but we never
actually see this output during or after the cache preparation step
takes place. It's useful to log what exactly happened so we can look
for problems or find potential optimization opportunities so just log
the output to /var/log which is also being collected by the various CI
scripts.

Change-Id: I3d0ab31e052889b9ac03de9a3ccba680e840fca5

commit_message:
Remove deprecated volume apis from v2 volumes client

The APIs 'show_pools' and 'show_backend_capabilities' in v2
volumes_client are deprecated, and they are re-realized in volume
v2 scheduler_stats_client and capabilities_client. Now these two
deprecated APIs are not being used by any other projects, and it is
time to remove them from the v2 volumes_client.

Change-Id: Iaed636bffe912e424dbccb20c38946525af052db

raise the minimum version of whereto to 0.3.0

This release fixes a problem with 410 redirect rule parsing that allows
it to be used in the nova tests.

commit_message:
Migrating legacy jobs

Moving legacy jobs from openstack-zuul-jobs to manila
repository. In order for us to start reworking the legacy
jobs to native v3 jobs, we need to do so.
This is the first step as described in the manual
and will also make it easier to remove the in-tree
tempest plugin sooner.

Change-Id: I7c9fbbb22860a2d246a9e6cb834f7c87875344f0

Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: Ieed09601fad8a50093cd0a6b142e000d5aa49fbf

commit_message:
Removes agent mixin from oneview drivers

This patch removes the agent mixin interface from oneview
drivers and adds a flag based solution instead. Once a set
boot device operation needs to be performed, the operation
is stored to driver_internal_info until the server power
on. Before power the server on again, the operation stored
is performed and then the server is powered on.

Change-Id: I8dabf7ef1ff6e44c062310c5cb3509e545585c0a
Closes-Bug: #1503855
Co-Authored-By: Fellype Cavalcante <fellypefca@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>
(cherry picked from commit 8f45317d4345872c050b2fa347f7be033556d2f5)

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-01 03:16:19.000000000', 'message': 'Use ujson instead of jsonutils

ujson is much faster than json.
For more details, please check [1] & [2].

commit_message:
Use zuul v3 src location to install ARA

With zuul v3 the ARA git clone will be there if
the test is executed by the ARA repo, or if there
is a depends-on patch from ARA. This allows us to
simplify the conditional.

Change-Id: Id76b2084b1ba8df7bfddd4fbb4b0cbe9859fd849

commit_message:
Adds --overcloud-user option to upgrade-non-controller.sh

There is an existing UPGRADE_NODE_USER environment variable you
can override but this wires that up to the script cli as -U or
--overcloud-user. This is especially useful for split stack
environments where the default overcloud admin user is 'stack'
and not 'heat-admin'.

Closes-Bug: 1724550
Change-Id: Idb8f87119028480df49bd3ee8cc8e6ddd599fc72
(cherry picked from commit 9d56658f23036cb900ace76a3fcf0ccae4ad83ee)

commit_message:
Update house rules to reflect absence of meetings

Since the TC stopped having weekly meetings, it's no longer appropriate
to hold off discussion on things until the next meeting except in
extreme circumstances that merit scheduling a meeting. This patch
updates the house rules to reflect the new agreement on asynchronous
debating[1].

[1] https://governance.openstack.org/tc/resolutions/20170425-drop-tc-weekly-meetings.html#debating

Change-Id: I2cce285d7d7df338904b6aa8b71bd9ab51ca5081

commit_message:
Add OpenStack-Ansible metadata

We need to add openstack ansible information in the role
metadata to be able to track role maturity. With it,
we can create a role maturity table and take decisions about
role deprecations.

The role maturity state is "unmaintained", conformly to our
role maturity guidelines and the decision taken in our last
community meeting.

Change-Id: Ife751beac4b8eda1e90ca8aa00b9d718fa35a53f

commit_message:
Use ujson instead of jsonutils

ujson is much faster than json.
For more details, please check [1] & [2].

[1] https://blog.dataweave.com/json-vs-simplejson-vs-ujson-2887b2c128b2
[2] https://blog.ionelmc.ro/2015/11/22/memory-use-and-speed-of-json-parsers/

Remove legacy-grenade-dsvm-neutron-nova-next

This job is pinned to stable/ocata changes but since neutron's
newton branch is EOL it will no longer work, so just remove it.

commit_message:
Fix ovs flow of the remote IP rule is covered

When the remote security group and the remote IP are configured
at the same time, the remote IP rule is ignored.

Change-Id: Ia60a70e76f36fa22c180bc7d0acd34505c952989
Closes-Bug: #1728495

When e.g., create vm1 with sg1 and sg2(security group), and
create vm2 with sg2. If set port more than one security-group
,some rules will be becovered. It will appear this phenomenon
that vm1 can reach vm2 well, but vm2 can not access vm1.

Closes-Bug: #1728479
'}]
commit_message:
Fix ovs flow covering each other with ovs as firewall driver

When e.g., create vm1 with sg1 and sg2(security group), and
create vm2 with sg2. If set port more than one security-group
,some rules will be becovered. It will appear this phenomenon
that vm1 can reach vm2 well, but vm2 can not access vm1.

Change-Id: I58416c17aef2828dcd7c2e77151b1db40167ffa9
Closes-Bug: #1728479

commit_message:
Fix Swift Authentication for log commands when V2 authentication is used.

When V2 authentication is used, ``trove log-tail`` command will get
``Authorization Failure. Authorization failed``.

Fix swift authentication in v1/instances:_get_swift_client.

Change-Id: Iedb2828b30daf04a460d907195bd16b5487e7242
Closes-Bug: 1657324

subject: Use ujson instead of jsonutils
messages:
[{'account_id': 25903, 'date': '2017-11-01 04:22:04.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 25903, 'date': '2017-11-01 06:29:44.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 11391, 'date': '2017-11-01 07:50:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I'm happy that it's much faster and we will benefit by 10 nanoseconds when passing the tests.
But I don't think it is a good reason to add new dependency to the library. 

Instead of pushing ujson in all OpenStack projects I recommend to discuss it with oslo team and make this change in oslo_serialization itself: https://github.com/openstack/oslo.serialization/blob/master/oslo_serialization/jsonutils.py#L276"}, {'account_id': 25903, 'date': '2017-11-01 08:02:38.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

Hi Mike,
Thanks for your comment, I'll follow your suggestion.
Have a great day ahead :)"}]

commit_message:
Use ujson instead of jsonutils

ujson is much faster than json.
For more details, please check [1] & [2].

[1] https://blog.dataweave.com/json-vs-simplejson-vs-ujson-2887b2c128b2
[2] https://blog.ionelmc.ro/2015/11/22/memory-use-and-speed-of-json-parsers/

Change-Id: Ia8481b11a0011fa52ace31cfdff507c5b6b9d91d

commit_message:
Remove two unnecessary auxiliary functions from db api

Currently functions _get_collection_sorted_by_time and
_get_collection_sorted_by_name are used to specify default
parameters for 'sort_keys'. Unfortunately they do it wrong,
which leads to confusion and incorrect behavior of the system,
when _get_collection_sorted_by_name is used to sort by time [1],
when mutable is passed as a default parameter value and then
modified in the code[2][3] (that is one of the most famous python
anti-patterns [4]).

To prevent confusion and keep the code clean and simple it is
suggested to remove the functions and call _get_collection
directly, with setting default parameters for sort_keys.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/mistral/blob/stable/pike/mistral/db/v2/sqlalchemy/api.py#L528-L539
[2] https://github.com/openstack/mistral/blob/stable/pike/mistral/db/v2/sqlalchemy/api.py#L235
[3] https://github.com/openstack/mistral/blob/stable/pike/mistral/db/v2/sqlalchemy/api.py#L183-L184
[4] https://docs.quantifiedcode.com/python-anti-patterns/correctness/mutable_default_value_as_argument.html

Change-Id: I342763ac1474c28e462319f38ad46ddc0231b290

commit_message:
Remove unified queue from gate pipeline

Initially the intent for adding this was to better test
any patches for roles together before they merge, but it
has had the unintended side-effect of causing patches to
take much longer to merge (because they all get lined up
in a single queue, rather than independent queues) and
a lot more infra resources are used (because a patch
that fails at the top of the queue will result in all
subsequent patches restarting all their tests).

As discussed in the channel, we'd prefer to revert back
to the previous independent queue method of testing. It
has served us well.

Change-Id: Ie5f973b243e6914f4927fd9ca3afc60d45e2af18

The return value of function "get_agent_hosting_loadbalancer" is either
None or a dict. Most of the time, it looks good because it usually
returns None. But when multi neutron-server rescheduled the same
loadbalancer from a dead agent almost simultaneously, it might return a
dict, which would cause KeyError since the dict format is such like
{'agent': {'id': xxx, ...}}.

Change-Id: Iac0f99590146ef870a979a6b4ac28b69e9e186e4
Closes-Bug: #1668513
'}]
commit_message:
Fix KeyError exception in ChanceScheduler.schedule

The return value of function "get_agent_hosting_loadbalancer" is either
None or a dict. Most of the time, it looks good because it usually
returns None. But when multi neutron-server rescheduled the same
loadbalancer from a dead agent almost simultaneously, it might return a
dict, which would cause KeyError since the dict format is such like
{'agent': {'id': xxx, ...}}.

Change-Id: Iac0f99590146ef870a979a6b4ac28b69e9e186e4
Closes-Bug: #1668513

openstack-zuul-jobs so we can share playbooks with

Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Force memcached container log to file

We were relying on the sysconfig options to set the memcached log file,
however, this is not happening, as the redirection is being taken as an
option and ends up being ignored by the memcached command. So instead,
we set the redirection in the container template.

Change-Id: Ic94e3fd7884d518eb9558c53acdc6b294823cd0a
Closes-Bug: #1720183

This adds the MemcachedDebug flag which makes memcached logs verbose.
Also, the service now reacts to the global Debug flag.

Related-Bug: #1720183

Is there evidence this works and gracefully falls back to the prior release that has a wheel, or does it just die and say "can't find a wheel for version 1.2.3"?

at least in what i believe the first jenkins response here is [1] we're installing 1.11.1 from a wheel on our mirror so it must have been built already. 

reading the instructions [2] says

 Packages without binary distributions will fail to install when this option is used on them

which isn't clear about "packages with prior binary versions but not the latest".  From a glance, version resolver bits *may* respect this, it's not totally clear to me.

it also doesn't really help if ansible pins a > for a requirement without a wheel that we have to build.  and i also don't think pip checks for linked libraries (the actual .so), so maybe we're installing something that doesn't work?  But these are even smaller corner cases.

this has happened to us before, IIRC, so some solution would be good and why i'd like us to investigate it.  but i don't think just switching the error message and carrying hacks that don't actually work helps that much in this odd case.

So -1 for visibility.  if this is shown to work as expected, where a missing wheel for a latest package falls back to the the prior version's available binary install, i'm +2 on it

[1] http://logs.openstack.org/29/509429/1/check/gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-full-ubuntu-xenial/4883d43/console.html#_2017-10-04_12_48_33_108557
[2] https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#install-only-binary'}, {'account_id': 13252, 'date': '2017-10-06 10:01:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Took some searching on pypi to find a suitable example, but at last I succeeded:

$ pip install --only-binary chainercv chainercv
Collecting chainercv
  Using cached chainercv-0.4.5-py2.py3-none-any.whl
...

versus

$ pip install  chainercv
Collecting chainercv
  Downloading chainercv-0.7.0.tar.gz (449kB)
...

so that does indeed seem to work as expected.'}, {'account_id': 7118, 'date': '2017-10-27 05:17:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: -Code-Review

I just dunno about this ... is the cure worse than the disease?  this is a very infrequent issue when cffi releases come, and we're trying to focus on the ansible devstack job moving forward where this isn't necessary."}, {'account_id': 13252, 'date': '2017-11-01 07:36:07.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

O.k., let's just revert the original workaround in https://review.openstack.org/516872"}]

commit_message:
Install critical libraries only from wheels for ansible

We might break due to missing libraries when installing dependencies
like cffi from source. So install them only from wheels instead.

Implicitly reverts [1].

[1] I6e0eab8e6ea126eec4c2c0767229cb915338e486

Change-Id: Iafc773572143bad4fdc9b55c1c4d0df262af9313

ok, so we don't have any great generic way to have a package installed before this i don't think.

my thinking around the -1 is that this isn't really that safe, because later installs are likely to try updating this.

i think i'd prefer to see a hack in here to install the library

 apt-get install -y libffi-dev || yum -y install libffi-devel || zypper -y install libffi-devel || true

which should suffice until images with Ia588c55b73643d27bdc3dff57cb00c1748498b37 are available"}, {'account_id': 7118, 'date': '2017-10-04 11:13:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

note for reviewers; this is well before we've started.  the problem is like [1] and happens when we install ansible [2]

it only happens in the period where cffi has a new release, but hasn't put up wheels, and our pypi mirrors haven't built them yet either

[1] http://logs.openstack.org/06/509406/2/check/gate-dsvm-nodepool-py35-nv/44c1b29/console.html

Installing libffi-dev may be a better longterm solution, this one would work as a intermediate shortterm solution until new images are available.

commit_message:
Work around cffi install error

cffi-1.11.1 was released without wheels so we cannot install it because
of missing libraries. Install 1.11.0 as a workaround.

Change-Id: I6e0eab8e6ea126eec4c2c0767229cb915338e486

commit_message:
heat-dbsync: increase timeout to 15 minutes

Increasing the heat db-sync from 5 to 15 minutes.
During an undercloud upgrade, the database can be very big and the
dbsync needs at least 10 minutes to run. So we override the Puppet
default value of 5 minutes to have a timeout of 15 minutes for
production deployments.

Change-Id: I7720bd68a3d6044287ccdebf77086a86c51ddd8f
Closes-Bug: #1726959
(cherry picked from commit d5f6b8ea0fd5759679764c9e16075304d1ee7efe)

commit_message:
Update proliant-tools to support Gen10 Proliant servers

This commits make update to ssacli version to point to latest
ssacli release that has support for HPE P/E-Class SR Gen10 controllers.

Closes-Bug: 1721185

commit_message:
Fix trove schedule-list error

When I set parameter TROVE_BYPASS_URL in admin_openrc.sh,the cmd  schedule-list return error message.
Debug detail as follow:
[root@trove ~]# trove --debug schedule-list rds-120
DEBUG (shell:754) HTTPClient object has no attribute username

Change-Id: I09d1d65683409da38a299675d88b90b29e34ea78
Closes-Bug: #1677438

commit_message:
Remove publish-openstack-puppet-branch-tarball from post pipeline

We need to unwedge zuul configuration for while we move
publish-openstack-puppet-branch-tarball into openstack-zuul-jobs.
We'll be reverting this commit.

Change-Id: I01debc6aa6f2d3e3d33ecb181344eabca91317ed
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Create build-openstack-puppet-tarball

This job we'll be able to add into check / gate pipelines for projects
that want to test building a puppet tarball.

Change-Id: I9e62a4a68db94e1d3d1e718edf340aeb9fbaba2e
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Allow dnsmasq configuration to be overriden

With the current state, someone wanting to overrde the dnsmasq
configuration, could think that defining overrides would work.
However, there is no section headers for dnsmsasq and templating with
config_template never worked. We can use what's already included in
the template, and rely on the template module instead.

Change-Id: Icf6cf1c7b7feee893fd311403a284ae512011a2e
Closes-Bug: #1697981

commit_message:
Add new grenade gate for designate worker model

Designate will change the worker model as default from Pike.
We need to modify current grenade gate for checking upgrading from
pool-manager to pool-manager and add new grenade gates that check
upgrading from pool-manager to worker model.

Patch in Designate that enable worker model as default:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/434355

Change-Id: I341001a3975bf8c75bb29c970030566e5187c4d2
Co-Authored-By: Nguyen Van Trung <trungnv@vn.fujitsu.com>

commit_message:
Increase timeout for requirements propose job

The timeout of 30mins is too small for the number of projects that the
requirements update job has to handle. Increase it to 90 minutes.

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: Ifc120036a610bee95b324333dfbe4aff8ddd2c48

commit_message:
Move log collection to 'post' stage

To ensure that logs are collected regardless of whether
a job succeeds, fails or times out, we move the log
collection to the 'post' stage of the job definition.

As the job playbook only gets run in nodepool, we remove
the detection of nodepool in the log collection script
and also remove the trap which executes it so that it
is only ever run when executed in zuul.

Change-Id: I5ab31cc141804cbcb6d8721032a79d0c724fc0a2
(cherry picked from commit fd4db8ea906d60a21b44205f796c769eeb51a764)

commit_message:
Fix the wrong usage of new style class in metering

This problem will cause self.host to be overridden by cfg.CONF.host
instead of the passed host value when calling MeteringAgent.__init__(host).

Change-Id: I50c5136e1cf1eb0db28edd02129f963948a54741

commit_message:
Fix usage of the method ensure_dir

This patch is for stopping using the ensure_dir in namespace_driver, as
the neutron.common.utils.ensure_dir is deprecated for removal, also
ensure_tree(path, 0o755) from oslo_utils.fileutils is suggested to be
used to create a directory.

For more informations:
http://codesearch.openstack.org/?q=ensure_dir&i=nope&files=&repos=

Change-Id: If492dd559fb03a5956d3acfdad863d1bdec737f6

commit_message:
Shrink Tempest scenario manager copy

scenario manager in tempest plugin was copied from
Tempest to avoid any plugin break.

This copied version of scenario manager is using lot of
Tempest interfaces. Many of them are not stable and might
change which can break plugin.

For example - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/503875/3

This commit shrinks the scenario manager copy to keep
only required methods.

Change-Id: If2f089bc7adbdb69f539c568be6f962d804c9cf8

commit_message:
Fix script error in angular flavors table

The colon character ':' in the flavor data like
'os-flavor-access:is_public' causes problems when
used as keys to lookup data. It should be replace
with 'is_public' and we'll see the following in console.log.

830e26e34b64.js:1336 Error: [$parse:syntax] Syntax Error:
Token ':' is an unexpected token at column 17 of the expression
[os-flavor-access:is_public] starting at [:is_public].

Change-Id: I1b212e52511a45a35464a9579ca3bb364e3f4754
Closes-Bug: #1634320
Closes-Bug: #1680037

commit_message:
kolla-kubernetes multinode gate fix

The converstion from v2 to v3 changed the behavior to run the gating
script on just the primary to all nodes. This PS changes the behavior
back to the legacy behavior.

Change-Id: I77adee81ec07979376be811c435a92e4be3976d1

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: I5d2f87d6ee3b10f83affcd730e3d28ae18f7af94

ansible tasks.

* Add irrelevant-files to the osc-functional-devstack-base job
* Comment out the functional-n-net job as it is horribly broken for now

commit_message:
Zuul job updates

* Add unit-tips job to run unit tests with the same project master branches
  as the functional-tips job (mostly useful for the unit.integ tests)
* Add irrelevant-files to the osc-functional-devstack-base job
* Comment out the functional-n-net job as it is horribly broken for now
  until the replacement package-installed OpenStack is ready

Change-Id: I5acdcb0a2f0f0dfe488740ae0add36366cc0ee21

commit_message:
Update filters to support over-commit

The default filters that we have do not properly support setting an
over-commit ratio. This change makes it possible for us to set the
over-commit ratios as expected and instance scheduling is NUMA aware.

Change-Id: I33ae92e73b699d34d9382c65a74dc78ccab53ea3
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Remove test variable for service_name in panko.conf file

panko.conf depends on "service_name" variable, but when generating
panko.conf in ceilometer, this variable is not set.

Panko is a single process service, no need add such test. So simple
remove the if clause.

Change-Id: I5ba41046e35cd3fa00b8c22e1b4435acfaff5279
Closes-Bug: #1725159
(cherry picked from commit 791bf3d5fa47729604eda9d6318c031c0b612a1a)

commit_message:
Put the code of generating sharing RP combinations into a method

There is simple implementation for generating the sharing resource
provider combinations currently. Actually that simple implementation
doesn't works well, just put it in to a common method which used
to share code and will be fixed in the future.

Partial-implement-blueprint add-trait-support-in-allocation-candidates

Change-Id: I3fb76453b428d1575f848bc09ed7c1c69dad295d

I'm actually even more confused with this patch. Is there a reason you didn't want to just modify the existing function AllocationCandidates._get_by_filters():

https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/objects/resource_provider.py#L2439

Also, the AllocationCandidates object already has a field called provider_summaries that is of type ListOfObjectsField('ProviderSummary') so I'm confused why there is a need for a new ProviderSummaryList object class.

-jay"}, {'account_id': 5754, 'date': '2017-10-24 11:36:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Jay, actually, this ProviderSummaryList includes a list of resource provider which only have any resource in the requested. commit_message:
More caches: ProviderSummary, ProviderSummaryList

Build some caches for different kind of querying.

TODO:
* separate unittest for the cache
* use trait id instead of trait name in the cache. (this may needs us
  to build a cache just like _RC_CACHE)
* maybe we shouldn't use versioned object. Just use normal python
  object with some of handy data struct which is good for query.

Change-Id: I34b0496b8816b1e5fc8268f06286e918e1bec233
Partial-implement-blueprint add-trait-support-in-allocation-candidates

commit_message:
Add has_resources to AggregatedProviderSummary

The has_resources method will ensure the AggregatedProviderSummary
object include a specific set of resource class ids.

Partial-implement-blueprint add-trait-support-in-allocation-candidates
Change-Id: If1cc450592022be493a8921589945449eea49482

commit_message:
Re-order Zuul graphs

There is an easy correlation between the Executor load and the
amount of Running builds. By re-ordering graphs, we're able to get
them to show one directly above the other, making it easier to
spot trends in the data.

When they're in different columns, it's harder to see the
correlation.

Change-Id: I7706c3293fbd702695fb3e4e917e33ca947beef9

Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

Change-Id: I9783714fa96c1d344c2044466fcf33bb2b8d7943

commit_message:
heat-dbsync: increase timeout to 15 minutes

Increasing the heat db-sync from 5 to 15 minutes.
During an undercloud upgrade, the database can be very big and the
dbsync needs at least 10 minutes to run. So we override the Puppet
default value of 5 minutes to have a timeout of 15 minutes for
production deployments.

Change-Id: I7720bd68a3d6044287ccdebf77086a86c51ddd8f
Closes-Bug: #1726959
(cherry picked from commit a41331486265a6c257e7bef0624c8155b0d40139)

[{'created': '2017-10-31 12:57:25.000000000', 'message': "[placement] avoid case issues microversions in gabbits

If a gabbi file sets a default microversion by setting a header
'OpenStack-API-Version' with a value like 'placement latest' and then
later overrides that in an individual test with a header of
'openstack-api-version' the difference in case can lead to failure.

In the best case the failure is consistent.

In the worst case it can sometimes work, because the header shows up
twice in the request, and the last header wins, order in the headers
and the resulting list dependent on the vagrancies of python ordering.

The solution is to always use the same case, so this change updates
all use to be lowercase, to establish a precedent that future people
will be able to use as an example.

Note that gabbi is case sensitive here in part because of the
implementation but also because it provides the control and possibility
to test exactly this problem.

Change-Id: I1e89e231cf0d46d211d360cda091b33520f85027
Closes-Bug: #1728934
"}]
commit_message:
[placement] avoid case issues microversions in gabbits

If a gabbi file sets a default microversion by setting a header
'OpenStack-API-Version' with a value like 'placement latest' and then
later overrides that in an individual test with a header of
'openstack-api-version' the difference in case can lead to failure.

In the best case the failure is consistent.

In the worst case it can sometimes work, because the header shows up
twice in the request, and the last header wins, order in the headers
and the resulting list dependent on the vagrancies of python ordering.

The solution is to always use the same case, so this change updates
all use to be lowercase, to establish a precedent that future people
will be able to use as an example.

Note that gabbi is case sensitive here in part because of the
implementation but also because it provides the control and possibility
to test exactly this problem.

Change-Id: I1e89e231cf0d46d211d360cda091b33520f85027
Closes-Bug: #1728934

commit_message:
heat-dbsync: increase timeout to 15 minutes

Increasing the heat db-sync from 5 to 15 minutes.
During an undercloud upgrade, the database can be very big and the
dbsync needs at least 10 minutes to run. So we override the Puppet
default value of 5 minutes to have a timeout of 15 minutes for
production deployments.

Change-Id: I7720bd68a3d6044287ccdebf77086a86c51ddd8f
Closes-Bug: #1726959
(cherry picked from commit c82f25c8c13a4af22d139abec786845f6b61c458)

Initially the intent for adding this was to better test
any patches for roles together before they merge, but it
has had the unintended side-effect of causing patches to
take much longer to merge (because they all get lined up
in a single queue, rather than independent queues) and
a lot more infra resources are used (because a patch
that fails at the top of the queue will result in all
subsequent patches restarting all their tests).

As discussed in the channel, we'd prefer to revert back

has served us well.

commit_message:
Remove unified queue from gate pipeline

Initially the intent for adding this was to better test
any patches for roles together before they merge, but it
has had the unintended side-effect of causing patches to
take much longer to merge (because they all get lined up
in a single queue, rather than independent queues) and
a lot more infra resources are used (because a patch
that fails at the top of the queue will result in all
subsequent patches restarting all their tests).

As discussed in the channel, we'd prefer to revert back
to the previous independent queue method of testing. It
has served us well.

Change-Id: I2df5f24a7ce2cb2aadceb395088505b99f31bd5c

commit_message:
Fix key_manager in nova config for Queens

keymgr_api_class is now deprecated in favor of keymgr_backend, with
full backward compatibility for users.
keymgr_backend is set to nova.keymgr.conf_key_mgr.ConfKeyManager
by default and configure key_manager/backend instead of
key_manager/api_class.

Change-Id: I7f4136ad32d70fe8a00e9147077224f9c4779b03
Related-Bug: #1725298

commit_message:
Don't open unused nova ports in iptables

Ports 3773 and 8773 were used for Nova EC2 API but are no longer in use.
The ports should not be opened in iptables.

Change-Id: I520c664a86be081b8d48675c22aa8d138aa9d1e6
Closes-Bug: 1726409

commit_message:
Revert "Don't run sync in upgrades"

Swift fails to deploy when using >1 storage node. The fact `need_sync`
was being set using information from ansible_local in an effort to
support rolling uprades sometime in the future. Sadly this variable
causes storage nodes to be removed from the key sync which results in a
failed build. If we decide serialized rolling uprades are required for
swift we can revisit this however until then we need to remove this
constraint and ensure we're allowing successfule deployments and
upgrades of swift.

This reverts commit 176452bebf7e1ceabd2cf72a89c558c0fc7f1420.

Change-Id: I21318d7c737c2415ef760b46176c3f9b372bb634

commit_message:
Remove legacy ceilometer api from undercloud

Ceilometer API is deprecated and disabled in pike. Lets remove
this starting queens as its not supported anymore.

Change-Id: I738e8743a315cc2865ba6d1e64c23498e911a283
