[{'created': '2017-10-04 15:53:34.000000000', 'message': "Bump fs.inotify.max_user_instances for scale

Since each dnsmasq process consumes one inotify socket, the default
value of fs.inotify.max_user_instances which is 128 lets us scale to
only around a 116 neutron subnets (a few other sockets are used by other
processes on the system). Since, we need to provide better defaults,
this patch proposes to bump this value to 1024 by default, while giving
the user a way to cahnge it. Based on
https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/13757 each inotify watch takes 1KB of
memory and we have fs.inotify.max_user_watches set to 8192 by default.
This means that even in the worst case we won't be using more than 8MB
of memory. Bumping the fs.inotify.max_user_instances value to 1024 is
safe because there is fs.inotify.max_user_watches which caps the total
number of files that can be watched by all the inotify instances a user
has.

Related Bugs:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1474515
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1491505

Change-Id: I39664312bf6cf06f1e1ca2e86ffd86fb9a4582ad
Closes-Bug: 1718266
(cherry picked from commit d2d0c3ff00de9b62382193d942239d543aa9499f)

commit_message:
Bump fs.inotify.max_user_instances for scale

Since each dnsmasq process consumes one inotify socket, the default
value of fs.inotify.max_user_instances which is 128 lets us scale to
only around a 116 neutron subnets (a few other sockets are used by other
processes on the system). Since, we need to provide better defaults,
this patch proposes to bump this value to 1024 by default, while giving
the user a way to cahnge it. Based on
https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/13757 each inotify watch takes 1KB of
memory and we have fs.inotify.max_user_watches set to 8192 by default.
This means that even in the worst case we won't be using more than 8MB
of memory. Bumping the fs.inotify.max_user_instances value to 1024 is
safe because there is fs.inotify.max_user_watches which caps the total
number of files that can be watched by all the inotify instances a user
has.

Related Bugs:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1474515
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1491505

Change-Id: I39664312bf6cf06f1e1ca2e86ffd86fb9a4582ad
Closes-Bug: 1718266
(cherry picked from commit d2d0c3ff00de9b62382193d942239d543aa9499f)

commit_message:
Fix puppet-agent install

The previous declaration where we installed the puppet-agent was after
we revoked sudo access. We need this to be part of the node setup so we
need to move it out of the build run and to the node setup playbooks.

Change-Id: Id68ee1b443a4172d0c1d6d58a04908c52a566623
(cherry picked from commit 536643ea9ca23220274d317c63baaf88021e0351)

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-31 15:44:26.000000000', 'message': 'Consolidate run & post playbooks for all tests

When zuul executes jobs it adds all the post plays together
and executes them in the inherited sequence. This is causing
some confusion in our cross-repo testing where the logs are
trying to be collected twice as the cross-repo test is based
on the standard functional test.

Instead of defining two sets of plays we can consolidate them
into a single set, eliminating the confusion and repetition.

At the same time we also do not try to collect logs if the
script to prepare them was not able to execute, and we fix
the conditional for the ARA report generation so that it
works properly with the value being given it by zuul which
is a boolean word. To make sure it still works outside of
Zuul we leave the conditional which uses the standard success
return code of 0.

Change-Id: Id5027415f33a7a41650332a983cb87fab7ba2a4a

commit_message:
Consolidate run & post playbooks for all tests

When zuul executes jobs it adds all the post plays together
and executes them in the inherited sequence. This is causing
some confusion in our cross-repo testing where the logs are
trying to be collected twice as the cross-repo test is based
on the standard functional test.

Instead of defining two sets of plays we can consolidate them
into a single set, eliminating the confusion and repetition.

At the same time we also do not try to collect logs if the
script to prepare them was not able to execute, and we fix
the conditional for the ARA report generation so that it
works properly with the value being given it by zuul which
is a boolean word. To make sure it still works outside of
Zuul we leave the conditional which uses the standard success
return code of 0.

Change-Id: Id5027415f33a7a41650332a983cb87fab7ba2a4a

[{'created': '2017-10-04 11:11:15.000000000', 'message': 'Ignore race conditions in finish with error

In case node_info.finished(error!=None) we want to make sure the error is
always propagated to the DB no matter possible race conditions.  Therefore
the node_info._version_id attribute is in this case reset to be fetched
from the DB rather than used during the look-up. Also perform an error
state transition in this case.

Change-Id: Iab3880a514e371f15a6b6a8558d3060c118ed3fc
Closes-Bug: #1721230

'}, {'created': '2017-10-05 11:08:04.000000000', 'message': 'Ignore race conditions in finish with error

In case node_info.finished(error!=None) we want to make sure the error is
always propagated to the DB no matter possible race conditions.  Therefore
the node_info._version_id attribute is in this case reset to be fetched
from the DB rather than used during the look-up. Also perform an error
state transition in this case.

This change also updates the error event processing to be done exclusively
by the node_info.finished() method to avoid races.

Change-Id: Iab3880a514e371f15a6b6a8558d3060c118ed3fc
Closes-Bug: #1721230
Closes-Bug: #1721233

commit_message:
Ignore race conditions in finish with error

In case node_info.finished(error!=None) we want to make sure the error is
always propagated to the DB no matter possible race conditions.  Therefore
the node_info._version_id attribute is in this case reset to be fetched
from the DB rather than used during the look-up. Also perform an error
state transition in this case.

This change also updates the error event processing to be done exclusively
by the node_info.finished() method to avoid races.

Change-Id: Iab3880a514e371f15a6b6a8558d3060c118ed3fc
Closes-Bug: #1721230
Closes-Bug: #1721233

commit_message:
Specify vars after children sections

Changes how the vars and children sections are ordered in the generated
static inventory by tripleo-ansible-inventory. Due to a change in
ansible 2.4, having them in the opposite order caused no hosts to match
the inventory.

See also:
https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/32196

Change-Id: I2aa1a04ea8a963b9c613008c12b1efffd365ceaf
implements: blueprint ansible-config-download
Closes-Bug: #1729058

commit_message:
Ensure nova is started after everything else

With recent versions of nova+libvirt-bin on ubuntu 14.04 there's a race
condition where nova-compute is started before libvirt-bin. If this
happens the nova compute process will stacktrace and never recover.
To resolve the issue we instruct the init config, when using upstart,
to only start nova after all other RCs have completed.

Depends-On: Ia3009901d63068b379f22d587efcba996f47b844
Change-Id: I7961110fc55fc551a62c41a6493a5144cbf40b95
Co-Authored-By: Chris Breu <chris.breu@rackspace.COM>
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Use Q_ML2_USE_QOS to configure QoS

Add the Q_ML2_USE_QOS option to simplify enabling the Neutron
QoS feature. If not defined, Q_MLS_USE_QOS defaults to False.
If it is set to True, devstack will setup neutron.conf and
ml2_conf.ini files to enable QoS.

Change-Id: I5e2790b8b46a2e228e10601910bf5ec8dd5bc589

commit_message:
Fix a tempest deprecation warning

Function 'tempest.test.services()' has moved to
'tempest.common.utils.services()' in version 'Pike' and will be removed in a
future version.  This patch corrects this deprecation warning in the legacy
neutron LBaaS tempest tests.

commit_message:
Add back debian support

We cannot build python-qpid-proton pip package on debian due to it
having 1.1.0 openssl. This seems like a lesser used package, so for now
we will just skip building it and give the world some time to resolve
the issue.

Change-Id: I4af88cb57ce2fc614d373c83cf3745c4aaaa5c7b

commit_message:
Switch to python-cffi for rpm based distros

Note that latest version of python-cffi is provided
from CentOS base and is python-cffi instead of python2-cffi.

According to CentOS/RDO packaging rules, all python2-XXX
packages has a provides on python-XXX, so when installing
it, python-XXX should always be used as it will install the
right package.

Change-Id: Ie30901c64993a6031278812e5072046a50371b3d
Closes-Bug: #1728915

commit_message:
Handle ldap size limit exeeded exception

LDAP servers have sizelimit configuration to limit the number of
user/group objects that can be returned for an LDAP query. This
change catches the size limit exceeded exception when users/groups
returned from ldap search query exceeds the configured limit and
responds with an appropriate error message instead of default
500 error message.

Change-Id: I9949bb7d458b4b037616c701e0e4d362bfa36473
Closes-Bug: #1712415
(cherry picked from commit f776fc18383fcfdc97932eaaab261a0b85e0ef68)

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: Ie1fdd384cd1448b01e1b40aba0eb19810a997d22

Use oslo_cache in auth_token middleware

Use the new oslo.cache library instead of using memcached directly.

commit_message:
SUSE: Fix copying repositories from the host

The repositories were missing the .repo extension from the filename so
none of them was copied to the container chroot. Moreover, we should pass
the zypper repository directory as argument to the 'find' command and not
the repository files themselves.

To prevent chicken and egg situations, we make the cross-repo test
non-voting.

Change-Id: Iab6f0c408edaf237ad022242c9d6d20257deff1a

commit_message:
Logstash jobs treat gz and non gz files as identical

We compress log files early so that we minimize network traffic and disk
storage requirements. But logically foo.txt and foo.txt.gz are identical
for our purposes when hosting log files. You can ask apache for either
and should get the same content.

This creates problems when indexing logs because we had been treating
the non .gz suffix'ed files as the logical names but now we don't have
them in all cases in ES because we submit jobs for the .gz file
resulting in the name in ES having the .gz suffix. Additionally if we
have both foo.txt and foo.txt.gz on disk when we generate the log
indexing jobs we'll submit two jobs to index the same log file contents.

We can address both these problems if we early on treat the non .gz as
the "logical" name and only submit jobs for the no suffix names.

Change-Id: Id99d6bc58f94c197b567ec4080ab24715128d855

commit_message:
IMAGES_ALLOW_LOCATION Wrongly Templated As String

In the template file horizon_local_settings.py.j2, the
IMAGES_ALLOW_LOCATION value is being set as a string, when it should
be a bool.

Change-Id: I6589fe93abab76243d30136babaa7b1e95989243
Closes-Bug: 1727438
(cherry picked from commit 941398b22cb2f5be9eaa4131e876b10921b8e5b2)

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: I9b52f68cee57732fb3f664d0bf67b2508ceae061

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-31 14:56:29.000000000', 'message': 'Update aio job to use become and fix environment

The in-tree job definition did not pass the legacy ZUUL environment
into sudo or dump the ZUUL_ prefixed vars into zuul.env, so the
get-ansible-role-requirements script did not detect that it should
use Zuul provided sources when available.

This fixes the job definition in several ways:
1) The job definition no longer calls gate-check-commit using the
   sudo command. Instead become/become_user are placed on the task
   so ansible will handle the sudoing and we just call
   gate-check-commit directly now.

2) The zuul legacy environment is removed from the job environment.
   Only ZUUL_PROJECT is used in the integrated repo[1], so that is
   the only var we define now, and we do not need anything special to
   pass it into gate-check-commit since it is no longer running in
   a sudo wrapper.

As a result of these changes, the zuul.env loading code is removed
from gate-check-commit.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/openstack-ansible/blob/c3ce03873798cd4e71b3fdd4ee9a2eae4bf59d7c/tests/get-ansible-role-requirements.yml#L57

Change-Id: Id0fb8502029e3f996d2557bc09c3314cc884bba8
(cherry picked from commit 0405ec9f76203bce9e6e12e32ff516fe7b7df83e)
'}]
commit_message:
Update aio job to use become and fix environment

The in-tree job definition did not pass the legacy ZUUL environment
into sudo or dump the ZUUL_ prefixed vars into zuul.env, so the
get-ansible-role-requirements script did not detect that it should
use Zuul provided sources when available.

This fixes the job definition in several ways:
1) The job definition no longer calls gate-check-commit using the
   sudo command. Instead become/become_user are placed on the task
   so ansible will handle the sudoing and we just call
   gate-check-commit directly now.

2) The zuul legacy environment is removed from the job environment.
   Only ZUUL_PROJECT is used in the integrated repo[1], so that is
   the only var we define now, and we do not need anything special to
   pass it into gate-check-commit since it is no longer running in
   a sudo wrapper.

As a result of these changes, the zuul.env loading code is removed
from gate-check-commit.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/openstack-ansible/blob/c3ce03873798cd4e71b3fdd4ee9a2eae4bf59d7c/tests/get-ansible-role-requirements.yml#L57

Change-Id: Id0fb8502029e3f996d2557bc09c3314cc884bba8
(cherry picked from commit 0405ec9f76203bce9e6e12e32ff516fe7b7df83e)

commit_message:
Pin grpc to 1.7.0

1.7.1 was released and it's failing silently with an exit code of 1
which breaks the unit and beaker jobs[1]. Pinning to 1.7.0 while we
investigate and wait for a fix.

[1]http://logs.openstack.org/27/516527/1/check/legacy-puppet-unit-4.8-centos-7/609fcb5/job-output.txt.gz#_2017-10-31_07_01_17_753531

Change-Id: Ieffc6a1168b7617fb67a4a311eba65db8a3ab6de

commit_message:
Move subunit generate to oooq playbooks

Instead of deploying python-os-testr before having the repos (with
mirros) setup and be exposed to mirrors issue, let's deploy
python-os-testr and run generate-subunit later when repos is setup
on the undercloud.

Note: running generate-subunit is very specific to TripleO CI, I don't
see a reason of including these tasks in oooq or oooq-extras, but
it can be discussed in the review.

Change-Id: Ide66a786d52f15c34b4f42982a276965c55146d6

commit_message:
Use dynamic inventory

Use the dynamic /usr/bin/tripleo-ansible-inventory instead of the static
one we generated. Seems there was a bug/regression in inventory handling
in Ansible 2.4.0:

https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/32196

That causes no hosts to match "overcloud" in the playbook due to how the
output is ordered in the static inventory.

Change-Id: Idec2c12dab486ed1a3c5d6c175099998c0afcc0f

commit_message:
IMAGES_ALLOW_LOCATION Wrongly Templated As String

In the template file horizon_local_settings.py.j2, the
IMAGES_ALLOW_LOCATION value is being set as a string, when it should
be a bool.

Change-Id: I6589fe93abab76243d30136babaa7b1e95989243
Closes-Bug: 1727438

commit_message:
Add set_column(s) for ovs_idl backend

The create/set Commands allow one to pass the result of txn.add()
to a subsequent Command in a transaction to use the result of that
Command's execution. In this way one can create a DHCP Option and
then pass it to an lsp_add() command.

This change replaces the direct uses of setattr() with a version
that does the substituation if one of the arguments is a Command
instead of a normal value, enabling this behavior for all Commands.

Change-Id: I97e7cbff7e71f7e1f00342c724af963a411b6c5d

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-08-31 22:49:54.000000000', 'message': 'Add propose-project-config-update job

This hand migrates the job. This job used to be configured to run
specifically on a host with a proper ssh key, which we now deliver via
secrets. That secret is used / delivered in a parent role, which may be
used by a lot of projects, and thus also copies some legacy scripts
around. However this job is used by the project that the scripts come
from, so there is no need to copy them around. This change adds a
conditional so that the role to copy the scripts around can be skipped.

The job just re-uses the existing shell script, a full conversion to
playbooks can be done at a later time.

Change-Id: I0d56ad749e302cdcdb61c39e5a748a26edc2a286
Signed-off-by: Jesse Keating <omgjlk@us.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Add propose-project-config-update job

This hand migrates the job. This job used to be configured to run
specifically on a host with a proper ssh key, which we now deliver via
secrets. That secret is used / delivered in a parent role, which may be
used by a lot of projects, and thus also copies some legacy scripts
around. However this job is used by the project that the scripts come
from, so there is no need to copy them around. This change adds a
conditional so that the role to copy the scripts around can be skipped.

The job just re-uses the existing shell script, a full conversion to
playbooks can be done at a later time.

Change-Id: I0d56ad749e302cdcdb61c39e5a748a26edc2a286
Signed-off-by: Jesse Keating <omgjlk@us.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Include additional folders in zuul v3 git src path

Zuul clones projects to src/{{ zuul.project.canonical_name }}.
Additional folders within that path are needed in
`development_repo_directory` to properly set constraints.

Currently a constraint is only being set for 'src/git.openstack.org'
instead what's expected, each project folder within
'src/git.openstack.org/openstack'.

Change-Id: I04716328115ac02dc6fcde68b08d2533cc060df8

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: I7cea99f195de0119b7dc6ac907f9143f91c3caba

commit_message:
Pin grpc to 1.7.0

1.7.1 was released and it's failing silently with an exit code of 1
which breaks the unit and beaker jobs[1]. Pinning to 1.7.0 while we
investigate and wait for a fix.

[1]http://logs.openstack.org/27/516527/1/check/legacy-puppet-unit-4.8-centos-7/609fcb5/job-output.txt.gz#_2017-10-31_07_01_17_753531

commit_message:
[WIP] Fix /tmp/in_target.d mount point handling

When using a dedicated (user defined) /tmp mount point,
currently dib fails because the umount of the user
defined mount point (/tmp) is done before the umount
of the dib internal used /tmp/in_target.d.

This patch introduces the environment variable
DIB_IN_TARGET_DIR which is by default set to a directory
in root (/) not to be dependent to other mount points.

WIP because I'm not sure if this really solves the problem
or just moves it to another level.

Change-Id: I0c4e643c449359fde7b24df0ca34f4daf6b20f23
Closes-Bug: 1719102
Signed-off-by: Andreas Florath <andreas@florath.net>

commit_message:
DockerCephDaemonImage is now optional for Ceph deployments

Remove obsolete statement that it is necessary to set
the URL for the docker image to use but include example
to show how this parameter may be overridden. Link to
prepare-environment-containers so reader may easily get
more context on this parameter.

Change-Id: I84334eb996d043fc6bfc95575d183d46a88b373a

Add spec for XClarity Driver

This spec proposes to add Power and Management
capabilities for Lenovo's XClarity Driver.

Partial-Bug: #1702508

commit_message:
Fix glance storage init script error in k8s v1.8.x

A Secret of images-rbd-keyring.yaml is failed because of line feed.

Change-Id: I9ad8a3815a6158df19339b5977725c32cc71c559
Closes-bug: 1724229

commit_message:
Update aio job to use become and fix environment

The in-tree job definition did not pass the legacy ZUUL environment
into sudo or dump the ZUUL_ prefixed vars into zuul.env, so the
get-ansible-role-requirements script did not detect that it should
use Zuul provided sources when available.

This fixes the job definition in several ways:
1) The job definition no longer calls gate-check-commit using the
   sudo command. Instead become/become_user are placed on the task
   so ansible will handle the sudoing and we just call
   gate-check-commit directly now.

2) The zuul legacy environment is removed from the job environment.
   Only ZUUL_PROJECT is used in the integrated repo[1], so that is
   the only var we define now, and we do not need anything special to
   pass it into gate-check-commit since it is no longer running in
   a sudo wrapper.

As a result of these changes, the zuul.env loading code is removed
from gate-check-commit.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/openstack-ansible/blob/c3ce03873798cd4e71b3fdd4ee9a2eae4bf59d7c/tests/get-ansible-role-requirements.yml#L57

Change-Id: Id0fb8502029e3f996d2557bc09c3314cc884bba8

those events.

commit_message:
Fix waiting for target disk to appear

This patch is changing the _wait_for_disks() method behavior to wait to
a specific disk if any device hints is specified. There are cases where
the deployment might fail or succeed randomly depending on the order and
time that the disks shows up.

If no root device hints is specified, the method will just wait for any
suitable disk to show up, like before.

The _wait_for_disks call was made into a proper hardware manager method.
It is now also called each time the cached node is updated, not only
on start up. This is to ensure that we wait for the device, matching
root device hints (which are part of the node).

The loop was corrected to avoid redundant sleeps and warnings.

Finally, this patch adds more logging around detecting the root device.

Co-Authored-By: Dmitry Tantsur <dtantsur@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I10ca70d6a390ed802505c0d10d440dfb52beb56c
Closes-Bug: #1670916

commit_message:
Ensure all pre-cloned git sources are found

Currently the find task only looks at one level deep
for repo folders, instead of the required three levels
deep.

Using the find module does not give us the ability to
set the depth level we want to do the find down to,
so we use a find command instead.

Change-Id: I0b218fe276292e13dbb40ab38c9a167025d16e45

commit_message:
Update Deploy guides publication

OpenStack-Ansible and Kolla already have published deploy
guides, but it seems like they are not in the index page.

Updating project data for those projects should be enough to
get them generated into the
``https://docs.openstack.org/pike/deploy/`` index.

On top of that, OpenStack-Ansible also have a Queens
documentation published under "latest", so I am also adding it
to the list of the deploy guides. The names of those
deploy tools is also edited to match the names of Pike
deploy guides.

Closes-Bug: #1727779
Change-Id: I59b73eb3f5afc7ef5cdb64252d558b57ea26abf2

commit_message:
heat-dbsync: increase timeout to 15 minutes

Increasing the heat db-sync from 5 to 15 minutes.
During an undercloud upgrade, the database can be very big and the
dbsync needs at least 10 minutes to run. So we override the Puppet
default value of 5 minutes to have a timeout of 15 minutes for
production deployments.

Change-Id: I7720bd68a3d6044287ccdebf77086a86c51ddd8f
Closes-Bug: #1726959

commit_message:
Append group permissions instead of clearing them

We set the groups for the syslog user to be "adm", but this will clear
any existing groups. That will mess with permissions in cases where we
want syslog to be in other groups for the ability to handle a different
applications logging.

Change-Id: If267cfd2f3f8f182c396e3f2836ec7e1d572fe0a

Listing hacking in test-requirements is deprecated, as
it is a blacklisted linter and the global requirements update
bot wouldn't update it anyway. Instead use it just as a
dep on the pep8 tox env.

commit_message:
Modify the wrong command in config qos doc

The example of "detach a port from the QoS policy" is
wrong in config qos doc.

OpenStack client don't display info about "Updated" after
set or unset operation. Egg, associate the created policy
with an existing neutron port, or detach a port from the
QoS policy. It is the same as network.

Also, OpenStack client don't display info about "Updated
or Deleted" when we modify or delete rules from Qos policy.

Change-Id: Idbc1877e85a13faca150307b3e773c1ea5333b77
Closes-Bug: #1727132

commit_message:
Add bindep.txt file

OpenStack CI uses bindep to figure out which packages need to be
installed on the host. However, when a bindep.txt file is not
available, a default one is used which may or may not be good enough
for all cases. It's best to have control over the packages which are
going to be installed on the host and as such we add our own bindep.txt
file.

Change-Id: Idab36eb82d916183f2fb40d326d095c5a8ee34b2

commit_message:
Use zuul v3 src location to install ARA

With zuul v3 the ARA git clone will be there if
the test is executed by the ARA repo, or if there
is a depends-on patch from ARA. This allows us to
simplify the conditional.

Change-Id: I3b31fdadae62d8558dc995b15dd51d4ffa50bd78

commit_message:
VMware: fix memory stats

The total memory for the vCenter cluster managed by Nova
should be the aggregated sum of total memory of each ESX host in the
cluster. This is more accurate than using the available memory of the
resource pool associated to the cluster.
This patch also collects the maximum memory and maximum vCPUs for single
ESX host in the cluster which will be used in the next patch which
implements get_inventory()

Change-Id: Ic73fae6763a2c9370e633d55f2db1ba7b3868718

commit_message:
Autodetect insecure registry in container image prepare

This change automatically inserts the DockerInsecureRegistryAddress
parameter into the containers image environment file if the registry
is reachable and unencrypted.

This eliminates a documented manual step, which is also required
throughout CI. It has been done in tripleoclient so that it can be
backported. The dedicated workflow for
blueprint container-prepare-workflow will have its own insecure
detection.

Change-Id: I74586145c222921880402cec92bbaa5f10e8b972
Closes-Bug: #1722632
(cherry picked from commit 007db34bfcea19d902c19c93265691eb3b902d16)

[{'created': '2017-10-30 20:17:09.000000000', 'message': "api-ref: document caveats with scheduler hints

I noticed this while working on change
I49ffebcd129990f1835f404d98b51732a32171eb and I realized
the scheduler_hints in the legacy filter_properties
dict is a bit different than what's in the RequestSpec
object, namely that the request validation schema is
per-hint. Some require a single value, like 'group', and
some accept a list of values, like 'different_host'.

Given how nebulous scheduler hints are, we should probably
note these in the API reference for the parameter, especially
because scheduler hints should not be considered interoperable.

Change-Id: I74114fc56bee2bebf4a5f5d6823ec968cad9a8e9
"}]
commit_message:
api-ref: document caveats with scheduler hints

I noticed this while working on change
I49ffebcd129990f1835f404d98b51732a32171eb and I realized
the scheduler_hints in the legacy filter_properties
dict is a bit different than what's in the RequestSpec
object, namely that the request validation schema is
per-hint. Some require a single value, like 'group', and
some accept a list of values, like 'different_host'.

Given how nebulous scheduler hints are, we should probably
note these in the API reference for the parameter, especially
because scheduler hints should not be considered interoperable.

Change-Id: I74114fc56bee2bebf4a5f5d6823ec968cad9a8e9

commit_message:
Use OrderedDict to sort the hostname before the alias

With ansible 2.4 we need to define the hostname first
to be usable after with :children in the inventory
If not, the Controller name is unknown for ansible
intentory.

Closes-Bug: #1728733

Change-Id: Ie943138c2da5d6acab2a75db3afd8fdad7558de2
(cherry picked from commit 4518273685b5216f10a058a5326e680dab3731d2)

commit_message:
Fix minor documentation missing dependency

The cgroup-lite package which is a dependency for docker,
was not on the example command line, but is present in
the helper script. Since the documentation details manual
steps, we should include that the packages is required.

Closes-Bug: #1701258

> tony, are you saying that the requirements bot update would need to

 > consistant on this openstack wide?  If so, I agree.

No I'm saying that upper-constratints.txt is a generated file.  Changing the data will just get clobbered the next time the bot runs.

So when we make this change we also need to update the tool that generates the file so that we don't loose these chnages 24 hours after merging them.

The optional step is ensure that all projects use correctky canonicalized names in requirements files but that isn't strictly needed and if we ever land the per-project requirements that will go away."}, {'account_id': 6593, 'date': '2017-10-31 11:18:12.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

commit_message:
Use pypi names for u-c package names

For pypi, posix-ipc is the same as posix_ipc but i.e. openSUSE
relies on the original pypi name (in this case posix_ipc) so
use the original pypi names for upper-constraints.

Change-Id: Ic46205402da821110e0db0eddce2d5bf80ae8e46

I'd like to have logan's opinion because he wanted to reduce the amount of all group vars by "proxying" the var on localhost on the case it's shared by 2 groups. If more than 2, then all. Maybe we should formalise that. IMO this is good enough of a fix.'}, {'account_id': 7353, 'date': '2017-10-27 00:28:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

recheck'}, {'account_id': 17799, 'date': '2017-10-31 02:10:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

Yea basically instead of scoping stuff to "all" if it is only used in 2 groups I placed the vars on localhost's host_vars here: https://github.com/openstack/openstack-ansible/tree/master/host_vars/localhost

and then patch them into the group_vars scoped to the groups that need to consume them like this https://github.com/openstack/openstack-ansible/blob/c5c7388bdc1e6a229fc6de137e34c971a8827303/group_vars/neutron_all.yml#L36-L39

It works to keep the vars out of the "all" scope and limited only to the groups that consume them, along with documentation in the host_vars file detailing which groups are consuming the vars so we can always easily know if something OTHER than the namespaced role/group is using vars.'}, {'account_id': 7353, 'date': '2017-10-31 02:50:42.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 7353, 'date': '2017-10-31 02:51:38.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 17799, 'date': '2017-10-31 02:54:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Fix Ceilometer deployments

When deploying ceilometer and swift the both ceilometer and swift need
access to a few shared variables. This change uses the established
pattern which proxies the shared options through localhost hostvars
which allows the respective roles and playbooks to inherited the
required options.

Change-Id: I4cb12cbf0063928e52657125b007bbeaf175de19
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Add proxy environment vars to boostrap-aio.yml

The bootrastap-aio.sh script uses the bootstrap-aio.yml file to
provision an All-in-One setup but this playbook lacks of proxy
support resulting in timeout inside of corporate networks. This
change add support to networks that need to reach a proxy server.

Change-Id: I3b28b8a39d050ced0ebca5ffdfbe1a7b78b9a7f5

commit_message:
Update device metadata when attaching disks/NICs

This change ensures that we're updating the instance device metadata
when attaching or detaching instance volumes or NICs.

Unlike the other Nova drivers, we're including all Cinder volumes
in the device metadata, not just the tagged ones. The reason is that
this allows Hyper-V guests to properly identify attached disk paths.

Note that the disk mountpoints (e.g. /dev/sdc) are ignored by the
Hyper-V driver. Also, we cannot override SCSI identifiers, unlike
the Libvirt driver, which will use volume IDs as SCSI IDs.

Closes-Bug: #1723431

Depends-On: I7a4c242c80b5b3562bf9513deb89071b5bb5bf28
Depends-On: I6f2c6ecf71d3254d64bc24574619c18184d3d055

Change-Id: I6853b1d167fe675435f3fb8f1fdb0cf0b63bed65

commit_message:
Add the supports-rolling-upgrade tag to Ironic

This adds the "supports-rolling-upgrade" tag to Ironic.

Ironic started supporting rolling upgrades with upgrades from Ocata to
Pike [1]. The rolling upgrades process is docoumented [2], and is
tested in gate by the ironic-grenade-dsvm-multinode-multitenant test.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/releasenotes/ironic/pike.html#id5
[2] https://docs.openstack.org/ironic/latest/admin/upgrade-guide.html#rolling-upgrades

Change-Id: Idac919316a740218a8f21d7908414a1a790c73f9

commit_message:
Fix check-requirements

Fix check-requirements: The assumptions with remote branch are not valid
anymore with Zuul v3, the change is on the proposed branch, check against
HEAD^1 instead.

Use the command module instead of script to get stdout in the
job-output.txt.gz file. Zuul v3 currently will not record the output from script
module in that file, only when command is used.

Note that the script module copied the file to the remote system - the
system where the tests are run - while command does not do this. But
the command is already on the remote system, use correct path for it.

Co-Authored-By: James E. Blair <corvus@inaugust.com>
Change-Id: Ib44332b4daf63b9d3fca6eadf0b4825614ca4aeb

commit_message:
Select Thierry Carrez as chair

Given that Sean took over ReleaseManagement PTLship this cycle
I'm fine with continuing with the TC chair duties and producing
regular status reports for the TC.

If you are interested in taking over, please post a similar patch.

Change-Id: I1fc172a540a27a42fca0eea02282a1c9673f0b3f

commit_message:
Add image_member_quota to Glance API configuration

Allow the configuration of image_member_quota
in Glance API. This error blocks the ability
of sharing images if the default value (128)
is reached.

Closes-bug: 1724879
Change-Id: Idc72c85943baf3d720500d2c30a813663f2927da

commit_message:
Check root disk size when doing resize in API

in API node, we can do resize check if the root disk size
requested is lower than current root disk size to avoid further
action into compute layer, there is already a check for size 0
and this patch make the check wider.

Change-Id: Id364255090358c4f55c417d69efff6e03ea12685

commit_message:
Remove test variable for service_name in panko.conf file

panko.conf depends on "service_name" variable, but when generating
panko.conf in ceilometer, this variable is not set.

Panko is a single process service, no need add such test. So simple
remove the if clause.

Change-Id: I5ba41046e35cd3fa00b8c22e1b4435acfaff5279
Closes-Bug: #1725159

We have moved to Zuul v3 now, this change needs to be done differently now, for current status and more information, see 
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-September/122834.html'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2017-10-25 20:25:23.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Chandan, what's your plan for the initiative? We are diverging the two repos as we speak. It would be great if we can speed this up so that we don't face painful resync process later."}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2017-10-30 18:59:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

We have switched to Zuul v3 now, this change does not apply anymore.

Learn on how to update your change with Zuul v3 at
https://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/zuulv3.html .

Simplified:
* Job definitions can be in-repo; common job definitions are in
  openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs repository
* Job scheduling can be done in-repo for project specific changes,
  common jobs are configured via
  openstack-infra/project-config/zuul.d/projects.yaml

Read the above mentioned document for finer details.

Please decide whether this change is still needed and then adopt if
for Zuul v3 or abandon it.'}, {'account_id': 12393, 'date': '2017-10-31 08:59:59.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Use zuul v3 src location to install ARA

With zuul v3 the ARA git clone will be there if
the test is executed by the ARA repo, or if there
is a depends-on patch from ARA. This allows us to
simplify the conditional.

Change-Id: I3b31fdadae62d8558dc995b15dd51d4ffa50bd78

commit_message:
DS8K: update replication_status in generic group APIs

In create_group and create_group_from_src, DS8K driver forgot to update
replication_status of group and its volumes if their type have enabled
replication, this patch tries to fix them.

Change-Id: I64fad5ab20e5c368fc16ec72a57afe199284916f
Closes-Bug: 1708592

commit_message:
Use OrderedDict to sort the hostname before the alias

With ansible 2.4 we need to define the hostname first
to be usable after with :children in the inventory
If not, the Controller name is unknown for ansible
intentory.

Closes-Bug: #1728733

Change-Id: Ie943138c2da5d6acab2a75db3afd8fdad7558de2

commit_message:
DS8K: don't swap role after failover group

After group failed over, DS8K driver should not run failback in replication
target to swap the role of primary volume and secondary volume which will
fetch the changes in secondary volume to primary volume.

Change-Id: Ieb5278429658920e569fb39890c5708f2151374d
Closes-Bug: 1709537

commit_message:
Fix multinode tempest tests

* For server creation, use scheduler hints to select compute node
* Merge single and multi node tests (base on compute nodes count)
* Sync manager with current tempest version (should be trimmed out for
  networking-sfc use later)

Change-Id: Ib70a72049bdf18047c52e00fe0d527fc1bad6ec6
Closes-Bug: #1660700

commit_message:
update "opendaylight" tar

commit_message:
ceph-access relation added to the README.md file

the nova-compute documentation to have cinder ceph rbd support
for Openstack Ocata and newer releases.

commit_message:
XtremIO: fix fetching FC targets from X2 array

Previous versions of XtremIO had the type as part of the target name, in
X2 this convention was changed and a driver updated is required to query
the type from the target object.

Closes-Bug: #1702458
(cherry picked from commit 67facebe4d9996bcbe8b3aaffd0a0d78660649e7)

Change-Id: I5511ff6bd8ae8deacc6223bad7ce5b8ab1dae0e1

commit_message:
Add a Hosts panel to the admin dashboard

This patch adds a new 'Hosts' panel to the admin dashboard. This panel
is grouped in the 'Reservation' group. Only a list view of hosts is
currently supported.

Partially Implements: blueprint host-operation-with-dashboard

Change-Id: I691fa53de4de1e3fbf367eba2f997cd6cafba875

commit_message:
Remove deprecated availability zone from share model

When share instances were introduced to manila [1] the availability
zone property moved from the share model to the share instance model.
This property was deprecated but proxied from the share. Deprecation
messages print whenever an availability zone is accessed via the
share rather than via a share instance.

Always access availability zone from share instance rather than
share and remove the code to proxy access to it from the share.

[1] I326c00b8252f2630e72bb0c22ca294f79feee2be

Change-Id: I5b8ce86ec417d1942aab3aa7ac325f43e0a9468b
Partially-implements: bp remove-deprecated-share-properties

commit_message:
Fix ShareSnapshotInstance share_id property

The ShareSnapshotInstance sqlalchemy model has a share_id
property as follows:

@property
    def share_id(self):
        # NOTE(u_glide): This property required for compatibility
        # with share drivers
        return self.share_instance_id

Return the share id instead of the share instance id.

Closes-Bug: #1600784

commit_message:
Remove deprecated share_type share model properties

When share instances were introduced to manila [1] share_type and
share_type_id properties moved from the share model to the share
instance model.  These properties were deprecated but proxied from
the share.  Deprecation messages print whenever they are accessed
via the share rather than via a share instance.

Always access these properties from share instance rather than
share and remove the code to proxy access to them from the share.

[1] I326c00b8252f2630e72bb0c22ca294f79feee2be

Change-Id: I65ac9f6108834ba56f147f1f5adb0114f3bbab67
Partially-implements: bp remove-deprecated-share-properties

commit_message:
Handle API NotFound exceptions at WSGI level

In many places, the API code catches various resource
NotFound exceptions and converts them to webob.exc.HTTPFound
exceptions.

Remove this local exception conversion and instead bubble
the original NotFound exceptions up to the WSGI layer to
be handled by the WSGI fault handler.  This reduces
code complexity, improves readability, improves message
consistency, reduces the chance of losing information
in one-off messages, and reduces the workload for the
translation team.

See change [1] for the work in cinder which this patch
mimics.

[1] I09f98921fdc2400cc3f6056e59001100abe06920

Change-Id: I366f49005a3699d4d9013ff0898a4ffd01cbea25

Marios, thanks for pressing this point.  I think if we allow a change of dhss value in an upgrade it is indeed likely to break the deployment.  We should probably check for this change and fail the deploy fast with a clear message and we should make that check irrespective of whether we go through with changing the default value as in this patch.  Can you point us to where we should be making that check?'}, {'account_id': 9003, 'date': '2017-04-05 16:51:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 8449, 'date': '2017-04-06 10:39:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

> Marios, thanks for pressing this point.  I think if we allow a
 > change of dhss value in an upgrade it is indeed likely to break the
 > deployment.  We should probably check for this change and fail the
 > deploy fast with a clear message and we should make that check
 > irrespective of whether we go through with changing the default
 > value as in this patch.  Can you point us to where we should be
 > making that check?

This is a tricky one. It isn't about getting rid of or changing a parameter in which case we'd follow the usual one cycle deprecation period. Assuming you aren't backporting this, it would affect upgrades stable/ocata to master/pike. 

This param is passed straight through to puppet-manila https://github.com/openstack/puppet-manila/blob/master/manifests/backend/netapp.pp#L131 - *there* may be the best place for this kind of validation before applying config.

We *have* handled special case service upgrades issues as part of the upgrades workflow in the past (e.g. sahara going on->off with mitaka->newton and https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/blob/stable/newton/environments/major-upgrade-remove-sahara.yaml). This one though is about a specific config value and I'm not sure how we would detect that before the templates are passed through to heat. It may be worth reaching out to the mistral folks (e.g. dougal on irc) to see if we could add a validation as part of the upgrades workflow.

Again, this potentially affects ocata->pike right now ... that upgrades workflow is still being developed afaik (not personally involved). I'd say make some more noise about this (maybe worth mailing list post or bring itup on next weekly irc meeting https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/tripleo-meeting-items https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Meetings/TripleO ) and if you (plural, the folks working on manila & tripleo support) feel this is a more sane default then we should land it. In the very least we would need a specific note on the O-->P upgrade docs (don't exist yet, we have https://docs.openstack.org/developer/tripleo-docs/post_deployment/upgrade.html#upgrading-the-overcloud-to-ocata-and-beyond still) once those exist. If we can also add some check to the O->P upgrades workflow then great, otherwise not sure what else we can do."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-06-07 20:10:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

commit_message:
Change Manila NetApp DHSS default to false

Almost all current manila deployments with NetApp backend
set 'driver_handles_share_servers' to false so make that the
default.

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html

commit_message:
zuul.d: jobs.yaml: Use openstack-ansible-tests checked out path

The playbooks for cross-repo testing and post jobs live in the
openstack-ansible-tests repository which is usually cloned in
tests/common subdirectory. We should use that when calling these
playbooks from the regular roles.

Change-Id: Ifb170a289d45ddad1a2cebf025f5e66f45d2daa3

commit_message:
Set Kafka Broker advertisement hostname

Default settings only allow localhost advertisement by kafka broker.
with this update kafka broker will advertise devstack configured ip address.

Change-Id: Ie3a146598789d6f63bbf55c4847cc569231c9dec

commit_message:
Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

Change-Id: Id37c6f432052724fbf3007e4b8dcc542a69f908e

commit_message:
Add default configuration files to data_files

In order to make it simpler to use the default
configuration files when deploying services
from source, the files are added to pbr's
data_files section so that the files are
included in the built wheels and therefore
deployed with the code. Packaging and deployment
tools can then more easily use the default files
if they wish to.

This pattern is already established with similar
files for neutron, designate and glance as has
been mentioned in the related bug report.

Change-Id: I0bbb00b68fb73fe35aeeb06c0690249fd46b646f
Closes-Bug: #1718356

Straight forward change, backward compatible change

Handle plugins with empty schema

Some plugins (i.e noop plugin) have no schema. Allow them to recieve
nothing.

Resources failing to delete will bear an error_deleting status.

'}, {'created': '2017-07-26 05:21:39.000000000', 'message': 'Composite paste for monasca-log-api

Following commit introduces using composite
paste file to describe application pipelines.
With the help of composite feature it was possible to
define 3 distinct supapplications, each having different
pipeline setup:

* version_app => no keystoneauth, simple data return with error trap
* healthcheck_app => no keystoneauth, simple data return with error trap
* api_v2 => as it was, added error_trap though

Following approach opens up the possibilities of modelling an API
in far more flexible way and removes the need of any hacking inside
the codebase.

Note:
Keeps backward compatibility with older codebase.

Extra:
* removed dirty hack around skipping certain request.path
in keystonemiddleware (now described in paste file)
* removed 404 when issuing ```curl api_host:api_port/```. Request
is redirected down to VersionApp

Change-Id: If89876de613a919e3594280fc801120f6bab9ff3

commit_message:
Composite paste for monasca-api

Following commit introduces using composite
paste file to describe application pipelines.
With the help of composite feature it was possible to
define 3 distinct supapplications, each having different
pipeline setup:

* version_app => no keystoneauth, simple data return with error trap
* healthcheck_app => no keystoneauth, simple data return with error trap
* api_v2 => as it was, added error_trap though

Following approach opens up the possibilities of modelling an API
in far more flexible way and removes the need of any hacking inside
the codebase.

Note:
Keeps backward compatibility with older codebase.

Extra:
* removed dirty hack around skipping certain request.path
in keystonemiddleware (now described in paste file)
* removed 404 when issuing ```curl api_host:api_port/```. Request
is redirected down to VersionApp

[{'created': '2017-10-14 18:50:54.000000000', 'message': 'Move FakeKeystoneClient to common

Add the ability to consume FakeKeystoneClient class as a common
module. This avoids extra dependencies on the Python mox/mox3
libraries at runtime and allows the end user to wire in the
custom class by simply making the following config setting:

  keystone_backend = heat.common.fakes.FakeKeystoneClient

This use case for this is the TripleO undercloud installer which
uses a heat-all process to transform heat templates into Ansible
playbooks. Previously we leveraged a "fake_keystone" service
as multiple applications and binaries required keystone dependencies.
(Both Heat, os-collect-config, and some openstackclients wanted
 a fully version of keystone running)

Now that we've streamlined these dependencies allowing heat to use
a fake KeystoneClient library shim instead of the full fake_keystone
process is much lighter and avoids the security concerns of the extra
socket. This patch allows us to do all of this without installing extra
test time dependencies on mox/mox3.

Change-Id: I03f1789957ba157871fd13164592116d7fcdabe4
Closes-bug: #1723639

commit_message:
Move FakeKeystoneClient to engine.clients

Add the ability to consume FakeKeystoneClient class as a client
module. This avoids extra dependencies on the Python mox/mox3
libraries at runtime and allows the end user to wire in the
custom class by simply making the following config setting:

  keystone_backend = heat.engine.clients.os.keystone.fake_keystoneclient.FakeKeystoneClient

This use case for this is the TripleO undercloud installer which
uses a heat-all process to transform heat templates into Ansible
playbooks. Previously we leveraged a "fake_keystone" service
as multiple applications and binaries required keystone dependencies.
(Both Heat, os-collect-config, and some openstackclients wanted
 a fully version of keystone running)

Now that we've streamlined these dependencies allowing heat to use
a fake KeystoneClient library shim instead of the full fake_keystone
process is much lighter and avoids the security concerns of the extra
socket. This patch allows us to do all of this without installing extra
test time dependencies on mox/mox3.

Change-Id: I03f1789957ba157871fd13164592116d7fcdabe4
Closes-bug: #1723639

commit_message:
Implement backend logic for project tags

This change adds in tags as a hybrid property for projects.
Also adds in relevant tests for backend logic.

Change-Id: Ie153130b794e3541f197f8fa1e73bf30a64f12dc
Partially-Implements: bp project-tags
Co-Authored-By: Jaewoo Park <jp655p@att.com>
Co-Authored-By: Nicolas Helgeson <nh202b@att.com>
Depends-On: I00f094a5584be40ab477cbf680a5f6d1afb4d21b
Depends-On: Ib3db74cb08e7fdec01d55d8988e0906948d80a32

commit_message:
Remove specific project checking in test

In test_create_is_domain_project, the test would check
for a specific project object within a list of returned
projects. If a new resource attribute is added to
projects, such as "tags", this test will fail due to
the sample project not containing the "tags" atttibute.

If we simply add a "tags" attribute to the sample project
generation, then the test will still fail for anything before
"tags" is added to keystone. After tags is added, this test
would also still potentially fail due to how tags is treated
as a list of strings, which is not guarenteed to be in order.

If two instances of the same project contained the same tags,
but not in the same order, they would be considered not equal
when compared. This would cause this test to fail randomly.

This change removes the checking of a specific project in a
list of projects to checking if the project ids match similar
to how domains are compared below this check. This prevents this
test from failing whenever an attribute of project is changed or
if the attribute is a list with no guarenteed order.

Change-Id: I00f094a5584be40ab477cbf680a5f6d1afb4d21b
Partially-Implements: bp project-tags

Remove unnecessary class method "get_create_params"

Instead of creating a method for updating a dictionary
we can use update method for this purpose.

for monascaclient and replaces it with osc_lib.command
extensions.

That change allows to benefit from numbers of builtin
formatters and enhancements already provided by underlying
libraries.

Another benefit is opening up the possibility of integrating
`cliff.sphinx` extensions that will aid with auto-documenting
the client commands for the Openstack documentation.

commit_message:
Migrate commands to osc-lib

Removes function based approach of defining the commands
for monascaclient and replaces it with osc_lib.command
extensions.

That change allows to benefit from numbers of builtin
formatters and enhancements already provided by underlying
libraries.

Another benefit is opening up the possibility of integrating
`cliff.sphinx` extensions that will aid with auto-documenting
the client commands for the Openstack documentation.

Change-Id: I2f8b561fb76a3b9548b46be23d779ae2efa4d9ce

commit_message:
Properly sort Heat stacks on Created field

replace the 'timesince_or_never' filter with 'timesince_sorted' one as the
creation_time attribute of a Heat stack can not actually be None.
Also add a 'timesince' data-type to this field.

Change-Id: I9727254b4c255331562083f957133ed6e3cd7e90
Closes-Bug: #1713748
(cherry picked from commit bfd66305ce7f8240a04eacf4f6349f2c7186ab90)

commit_message:
Replace the usage of some aliases in tempest

In tempest, following aliases have been moved in version Pike
and will be removed in version Queens:
* manager > os_primary [1]
* admin_manager > os_admin [2]
* os_adm > os_admin [3]
* os > os_primary [4]
* alt_manager > os_alt [5]

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/468036/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/467852/
[3] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/467605/
[4] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/466991/
[5] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/457555/

Change-Id: I864d59a2e72a1d690f055bebc1e123f38b28f205

commit_message:
Call base from_dict in RequestContext

This changes the from_dict override to call the base class
implementation with the Congress-specific keys passed as kwargs.
It should prevent issues where a new key is added to the base to_dict
function that is not an accepted parameter on the constructor.

Change-Id: I271111f1fe2ba0d4350e94f672abd327ac8eeb7a
Closes-Bug: 1721432

commit_message:
Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

Change-Id: I9760e93bfcd8a175bb97a8ee55ce9ff19d8d3923

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-22 03:01:36.000000000', 'message': 'Add security headers to web accessable services.

Adds the following headers as static:

    X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff"
    X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block"
    append Content-Security-Policy "default-src 'self' https: wss:;"

nosniff prevents non-executable mime times from becoming executable.
The X-XSS-Protection header will prevent the loading of a page if the
browser detects an xss attack.  The Content-Security-Policy declares
what dynamic resources are allowed to load.

Adds the following header as user-setable via the
keystone_x_frame_options variable.

    X-Frame-Options "DENY"

By default the X-Frame-Options header denies embedding in an iframe.

Change-Id: Iadd3e93bdb7e9d41ae1d027196367448dbce19f1
Partial-Bug: 1717321

commit_message:
Add security headers to web accessable services.

Adds the following headers as static:

    X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff"
    X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block"
    append Content-Security-Policy "default-src 'self' https: wss:;"

nosniff prevents non-executable mime times from becoming executable.
The X-XSS-Protection header will prevent the loading of a page if the
browser detects an xss attack.  The Content-Security-Policy declares
what dynamic resources are allowed to load.

Adds the following header as user-setable via the
keystone_x_frame_options variable.

    X-Frame-Options "DENY"

By default the X-Frame-Options header denies embedding in an iframe.

Change-Id: Iadd3e93bdb7e9d41ae1d027196367448dbce19f1
Partial-Bug: 1717321
(cherry picked from commit 81a28142a065e07f16756b1bc4cfb68a98e0a2e9)

commit_message:
use ml2 driver api from neutron-lib

The ml2 plugin driver API was rehomed into neutron-lib with commit
Ifc829953ef4d5859c3475903965dc08aba42fd9c and the API was shimmed in
neutron with I86a10091b55d1123e8d16f16155e0312bb10e54c. In prep for
neutron consumption Ice49572e217eeaf820e48d40f2251d08766490b5 this
patch switches over to lib's version of the respective code.

Change-Id: I957c89b4e4f0f8f8ba31929db033eba77822523e

commit_message:
Expose allowing setting log files for apache vhost

Being able to set the log files for the apache vhost was done in a
recent commit [1]. However, that commit missed exposing the
configuration in the service-specific manifests. This adds that.

[1] Ic2ffef73f6a12d6225f87d285003c3deb7541126

Change-Id: Iae6a86cb93305cb3307e058cfd31e0fca3b1be8e

commit_message:
Database session need to rollback after duplication

When a session is first used for accessing database but fails, it
need to rollback before being used again.

Change-Id: I82065e4add3a9a5d0906734bb124617658491c31
Closes-bug: #1727667

commit_message:
Change checkout for nova-lxd to use the EOL tag

The nova-lxd repo no longer maintains a stable/newton branch. This
change updates our checkout in developer mode to use the "newton-eol"
tag.

Depends-On: Ia3009901d63068b379f22d587efcba996f47b844
Change-Id: Ica08c8815c087154dc42a46de197ad1a2d398dfb
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

 > to https://bugs.launchpad.net/tripleo/+bug/1728158 -- now that it's
 > fixed, this might pass the gates.

openvswitch 2.8.1 is not working and looks like there is fix [1] in openstack-selinux(which is not installed in selinux enabled undercloud)

[1] https://github.com/redhat-openstack/openstack-selinux/commit/9d30e36cea34027f6e4cda7fb190c2c989223f18"}, {'account_id': 16312, 'date': '2017-10-30 09:22:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

> there is selinux denial which should be fixed by the latest
 > openstack-selinux which is not installed on undercloud?!?

Yeah, openvswitch is being installed as transitive dependency for tripleoclient. However openstack-selinux is not a dependency, so it's not being installed. I'm not sure where the right fix is:

- Adding openstack-selinux as dependency for tripleoclient
- Adding openstack-selinux as dependency for openvswith
- Adding openstack-selinux explicit installation in oooq with tripleoclient"}, {'account_id': 16312, 'date': '2017-10-30 09:34:40.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 16312, 'date': '2017-10-30 10:07:39.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 10969, 'date': '2017-10-30 10:59:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

@Alfredo, I don't think we need to solve this in oooq. Dependencies should be handled in packaging."}, {'account_id': 13861, 'date': '2017-10-30 11:00:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

recheck'}, {'account_id': 1955, 'date': '2017-10-30 11:01:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

It's a soft dep, so cannot be explicitly required by either tripleoclient or openvswitch.
If undercloud needs to be selinux enabled, openstack-selinux must be installed explicitly by the UC installer, whatever that it."}, {'account_id': 10969, 'date': '2017-10-30 11:33:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

@Alan, it seems like tripleoclient issue - to ensure that openstack-selinux is installed if it should be selinux enabled. Anyway, oooq is not the place to solve such dependencies issues IMHO.'}, {'account_id': 16312, 'date': '2017-10-30 11:37:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

recheck'}, {'account_id': 20970, 'date': '2017-10-30 11:39:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

I have literally just run into this issue when using oooq to try and deploy to RDO Cloud.  It's failing because selinux python bindings aren't installed.  I'd like to open a bug to track this but I'm not sure where it should go either."}, {'account_id': 8652, 'date': '2017-10-30 11:43:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

I'm opening a bug about this against tripleo-client"}, {'account_id': 16312, 'date': '2017-10-30 11:46:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

> @Alan, it seems like tripleoclient issue - to ensure that
 > openstack-selinux is installed if it should be selinux enabled.
 > Anyway, oooq is not the place to solve such dependencies issues
 > IMHO.


Note that openstack-selinux is installed properly by "openstack undercloud install" command as part of dib execution. Failure in this case is specific to the workflow in CI environment so fixing this in oooq is not so crazy, IMHO

Said this, according to https://docs.openstack.org/tripleo-docs/latest/install/installation/installing.html undercloud installation is recommended with selinux enforcing and unsupported with disabled so i think adding it as a requirement for tripleoclient can be adequate.

@Alan, what do you think?'}, {'account_id': 16312, 'date': '2017-10-30 12:12:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

> > @Alan, it seems like tripleoclient issue - to ensure that
 > > openstack-selinux is installed if it should be selinux enabled.
 > > Anyway, oooq is not the place to solve such dependencies issues
 > > IMHO.
 > 
 > 
 > Note that openstack-selinux is installed properly by "openstack
 > undercloud install" command as part of dib execution. Failure in
 > this case is specific to the workflow in CI environment so fixing
 > this in oooq is not so crazy, IMHO
 > 
 > Said this, according to https://docs.openstack.org/tripleo-docs/latest/install/installation/installing.html
 > undercloud installation is recommended with selinux enforcing and
 > unsupported with disabled so i think adding it as a requirement for
 > tripleoclient can be adequate.
 > 
 > @Alan, what do you think?

Installing openstack-selinux is not helping to unblock this review as it installs openstack-selinux from last promoted repos which doesn't include fix for ovs. I think the only solution to unblock is rever ovs-2.8.1'}, {'account_id': 16312, 'date': '2017-10-30 12:44:55.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 10.'}, {'account_id': 1955, 'date': '2017-10-30 13:09:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 8652, 'date': '2017-10-30 13:42:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2017-10-30 14:47:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Workflow+1'}]

commit_message:
switch to RDO Queens deps repo

Starting with RDO Queens, dependencies will be maintained during
the development in a repository on trunk.rdoproject.org.
Repo will be versioned in the future, for now we are using
"latest" symlink.

Change-Id: I4c8295fbf1021bd3cdcaba2030339e002327fa34

commit_message:
Fix issue with different decimal separators

An issue was discovered in the ZFSonLinux driver wherein on a system
set to have a locale where the decimal separator is not a period but
rather a comma the method translate_string_size_to_float() would fail
because it's regex to find sizes in strings did not account for any
other decimal separators other than periods.

This fix updates the regular expression to accept either a period or
a comma as a decimal separator in a size string.

Many thanks to Dr. Clemens Hardewig for reporting the original bug
and providing an updated regular expression.

Change-Id: I15da4aaff90814eed03816db013d6acc89ba2ee8
Closes-Bug: #1714691
(cherry picked from commit 8800e54f770c4c4a6f813a5ea72bb12316482d87)
(cherry picked from commit 776015af4000a48640bd0a91f7220b49c18238d9)

commit_message:
apache wsgi: Exchange defaults for workers and threads

Due to Python's GIL [1], we can't use multiple threads for running
OpenStack services without a performance penalty, since the execution
ends up serialized, which defeats the purpose.

Instead, we should use several processes, since this approach doesn't
have this limitation.

[1] https://wiki.python.org/moin/GlobalInterpreterLock

Change-Id: Ibdb5bf1e533e40449340e7c3049db4c338c28e47

commit_message:
Container action response 500

Zun action APIs (i.e. exec, top, etc.) will return 500 if Docker
return 409 (Conflict). Below are observations:

* Docker will validate container state before executing a specific
action, and raise state conflict (409) error if the state of the
container doesn't allow the action to perform. For example,
'exec' is not allowed if container is on state 'Stopped'.

* Zun will do a similar state validation in zun-api.
* Zun will sync the container states from Docker every 60 seconds.

As a result, the state in Zun and Docker might be different during
the 60 seconds interval. This 500 error happened if the state between
Zun and Docker is out-of-sync (sometimes in between the 60 seconds).
This makes the state validation passed in Zun but failed in Docker.

Change-Id: If1db262881ac89c62d5a2e7f3cfe67a09724ef5a
Closes-Bug: #1723499

commit_message:
Remove the local tempest plugin

The plugin has been split into its own repository [1] in accordance
with Queens Goal "Split Tempest Plugins into Separate Repos/Projects"
[2]. This patch removes the local copy as well as the setuptools
entry point.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/zun-tempest-plugin
[2] https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/queens/
    split-tempest-plugins.html

Implements: blueprint zun-split-tempest-plugins
Change-Id: Ibfeb38b52c05a9f886dc7524d892842971cbd264

commit_message:
Remove legacy-tempest-dsvm-nnet

The nova-network job can only run on stable/newton since
nova-network requires a cells v1 setup starting in Ocata.

Since we already have the legacy-tempest-dsvm-nnet-newton
job just remove legacy-tempest-dsvm-nnet and replace its usage
with legacy-tempest-dsvm-nnet-newton.

Change-Id: I257d0dc84b59e4a71bfb7f71b50f38fbe861278d

commit_message:
Added OS_AUTH_TYPE parameter to auth file

Some services like Gnocchi can not get proper endpoint from
Keystone service.
Exporting variable: OS_AUTH_TYPE with value 'password'
will fix the problem.

Change-Id: I96aa50f152297dd406c505de1305fe6c796e7f96
(cherry picked from commit c8a4e3cb2b7d7b6ef6a6aa569d1f9fda68b26e34)

commit_message:
[Docs] Fix links to inventory docs

The documentation on generating inventory was referenced as
'generate-inventory' in a table of contents index but the actual file
was named 'inventory' so it was never listed. The file has been renamed.

Also, a page in the developer docs included duplicated information from
the inventory docs. That page has been deleted and the link to it has
been replaced with one to the more complete inventory docs.

Change-Id: I6e1cda1daa1931c925b93872565994109216e7ea

commit_message:
Revert "Move log collection to 'post' stage"

This reverts commit fd4db8ea906d60a21b44205f796c769eeb51a764.
The playbook used here needs to be in every repo calling that job
(which is all our branches and all our repos).

I suggest we revert it until alll the other zuul v3 changes are settled.
We can then take a more organized approach.

Change-Id: I8ba967af69311fc0684635462d27cdc03728ca81
(cherry picked from commit af3a08a5b1f14e61957f5f84c5dfdab2ddfb7279)

commit_message:
use ml2 driver api from neutron-lib

The ml2 plugin driver API was rehomed into neutron-lib with commit
Ifc829953ef4d5859c3475903965dc08aba42fd9c and the API was shimmed in
neutron with I86a10091b55d1123e8d16f16155e0312bb10e54c. In prep for
neutron consumption Ice49572e217eeaf820e48d40f2251d08766490b5 this
patch switches over to lib's version of the respective code.

Change-Id: If6e20cf90cdf61a05a499f1251376db498e5e7c0

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-28 07:26:49.000000000', 'message': "Fix container mac generation and remove extra tasks

The container create role will fail when adding a new network
to an existing set of container. The role attempts to read the hwaddr
file prior to its existence due to our use of local_facts. This change
simplifies how the mac addresses are generated by using a block / rescue
which will simply consume the known mac address from the container when
needed or fall back to the generation tasks as needed.

While working on this issue I noticed that we were still using a
pre-Ansible 2.0 failure notice which is no longer relevant as we've been
using Ansible 2.x for quite a while now. The old assertion has been
removed.

A new assertion has been added to notify the deployer that the
physical_host variable must be set to use this role.

Change-Id: Ic2800f1c17d10180e4e9a7be7f9b435ff8cc5487
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Fix container mac generation and remove extra tasks

The container create role will fail when adding a new network
to an existing set of container. The role attempts to read the hwaddr
file prior to its existence due to our use of local_facts. This change
simplifies how the mac addresses are generated by using a block / rescue
which will simply consume the known mac address from the container when
needed or fall back to the generation tasks as needed.

While working on this issue I noticed that we were still using a
pre-Ansible 2.0 failure notice which is no longer relevant as we've been
using Ansible 2.x for quite a while now. The old assertion has been
removed.

A new assertion has been added to notify the deployer that the
physical_host variable must be set to use this role.

Change-Id: Ic2800f1c17d10180e4e9a7be7f9b435ff8cc5487
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Fixes module not found error in NetScaler LBaaSV2 driver

NetScaler driver in LBaaSv2 was missing a module named ncc_client.
It was originally placed as part of LBaaSv1 drivers under
neutron_lbaas/services/loadbalancer/drivers/netscaler, but was
removed as part of Change-Id: I506949e75bc62681412358ba689cb07b16311b68
This fix adds ncc_client.py along with the driver and updates the
driver with correct path.

Unit tests were already existing, but some how __init__.py was
missing from the folder. With in tests, fixed couple of refference
to old code.

The backport had to be modified in order to pass PEP8 tests that
include the N531 test which was removed in a future patch:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/447921/

Translation hints were added to:
neutron_lbaas/drivers/netscaler/ncc_client.py

Change-Id: Iaeb2a1eef3e926bb9549d026770d38cdd56dc773
Closes-Bug: 1697761
Signed-off-by: Mohammed Salih Puthenpurayil <linusali@gmail.com>
(cherry picked from commit d2820ccc9e2bffa31a020b0f701ac460f3286fbf)

commit_message:
Shrink Tempest scenario manager copy

scenario manager in tempest plugin was copied from
Tempest to avoid any plugin break.

This copied version of scenario manager is using lot of
Tempest interfaces. Many of them are not stable and might
change which can break plugin.

For example - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/503875/3

This commit shrinks the scenario manager copy to keep
only required methods.

Change-Id: If2f089bc7adbdb69f539c568be6f962d804c9cf8

commit_message:
Fix non-cascade LB delete with children

When the user attempts to delete a load balancer, without the cascade option,
the load balancer is locked in "PENDING_DELETE" prior to the check for child
objects. The child object check will return the error to the user, but would
leave the load balancer locked in "PENDING_DELETE".
This patch corrects the order to do the validation prior to locking the
load balancer in "PENDING_DELETE".

Story: 2001256
Task: 5786
(cherry picked from commit c05a8cfb88bd1219a086e8826f7783b64f1e8537)

Change-Id: I7364e6dbe6f647962df892e4c72cfdf7598c502b
